there has been no news of the landing of the european Mars rover beagle ii .
( Agence france - presse , london , 1 st ) - Martian exploration program spokesman Barrett said that after a us satellite could not connect with the european beagle ii ( BEAGLE 2 ) landing craft that had landed on mars , the hope of deliberately collecting signals from the beagle ii could only be pinned on its mother ship , the mars express .
Barat said , &quot; We have not obtained any further results . &quot;
he said : &quot; now we have placed our hopes in its mother ship , the Mars Express , waiting for it to gather information . &quot;
the us - based odyssey spacecraft did not receive any information from the european mars probe beagle ii , which has continued to search for signs of life on mars since leaving the mars express for mars .
the Mars odyssey spacecraft was launched by the us space agency into the orbit of mars to carry out another exploration mission .
the european space agency , based in Paris , said that the european - made artificial satellite of the mars express has been launched into the extreme orbit of mars , and it is hoped that it will still be able to transmit some signals next week .
the puppy ii was originally scheduled to land on mars at Christmas , but its signals are still hard to fathom .
after leaving the mother ship mars express on december 19 , the beagle 2 became the first european spaceship to land on another planet .
during the 18 - day mission , beagle ii plans to test rocks , soil , signal transmission modes , or all life on mars .
scientists had boldly predicted that the british spaceship might be trapped in a hole .
Pakistani president Musharraf wins confidence vote in senate and house of representatives
( Agence france - presse , Islamabad , 1 st ) - Pakistani president Pervez Musharraf won a vote of confidence in both houses of parliament today with the abstention of islamic senators and a boycott by opposition parties . the vote of confidence confirmed that Musharraf 's rule will last until 2007 .
" Musharraf won a majority of the votes in parliament , " information minister Rashid told afp .
no congressman voted against him . &quot;
in the 342 - seat house of representatives , 191 members of the house voted for Musharraf , muslim senators abstained , and opposition parties boycotted the controversial vote of confidence .
Musharraf made concessions to six islamic party coalitions and agreed to resign as commander - in - chief of the army , while seeking approval from the supreme court within one month of the dissolution of parliament .
in the 100 - seat senate , 56 senators voted for Musharraf , and 42 muslim and opposition senators abstained or boycotted .
Musharraf took power in a coup in october 1999 and has since refused to step down .
former rebels to join military leadership
( Agence france - presse , Blondie , Buzombura , 1 st ) - president Ndayizeye of Blondie delivered a new year 's message to the nation today , saying that the post - war joint chiefs of staff meeting will be formed before next week and will include former rebel leaders .
the former " democratic defense force " of the rebel army welcomed this move and praised it as " an important step " towards the establishment of a new armed force .
President Ndayizeye said in a televised statement that the rebel fighters in the civil war in Brondi over the past 10 years must be settled by january 5 , and the new military leadership will be ready by january 7 , with four of them former rebel leaders .
Ndayizeye said : " the parties that signed the agreement ( on a three - year november cease - fire in Okinawa ) must settle down the cantonment of the fighters by january 5 at the latest . "
he added that the joint chiefs of staff meeting , including former rebel leaders , must be ready by january 7 .
the operation is mainly related to the largest of the six rebel organizations that signed the peace agreement , the " democratic defense force .
the seventh rebel organization , the " national liberation army , " refused to sign the peace agreement .
since the civil war broke out in 1993 between the Hudu rebels and the Tutsi government forces in Bulongdi , about 300,000 people have died .
China seizes 186 tons of us beef
( Agence france - presse , beijing , 2 nd ) - china 's state - run media , the beijing youth daily , reported today that due to market fears that imported beef might be infected with mad cow disease virus , the relevant authorities started meat market inspection operations and seized 186 tons of us beef in beijing yesterday .
Beijing youth daily pointed out that according to the proposal of the ministry of agriculture , the beef will be destroyed after inspection .
China was one of more than 30 countries in the world that suspended us beef imports last week .
all cattle related products , with the exception of milk and other dairy products , leather and photographic gelatin emulsion , are prohibited .
Beijing youth daily reported that the beijing agricultural bureau recently issued a series of prevention and control decrees and launched a comprehensive market inspection operation .
at present , there are no cases of mad cow disease in china .
the beef seizure was the second in nearly a week after authorities seized 60 kilograms of beef from the us state of washington , where mad cow cases were reported , from an american cargo ship in Ningbo , Zhejiang province .
although statistics from the department of commerce show that china imported 532 million us dollars worth of meat from the united states last year , the volume of us beef imports remains unknown .
from january to july last year , china imported a total of 316 million us dollars worth of meat from the united states .
North korea authorizes us delegation to visit Yongbyon nuclear facility
( Agence france - presse , washington , 2nd ) - the us newspaper today reported that Pyongyang authorities have authorized a us delegation including top nuclear scientists to visit the north Korean nuclear facility next week .
members of the delegation told the us newspaper today that the bush administration had approved the us delegation 's scheduled visit to north korea from january 6 to 10 .
it will be the first visit by a foreign delegation to north korea 's disputed nuclear facilities since un inspectors were expelled from the country a year ago .
members of the us delegation include a chinese expert from Stanford university , two senate foreign policy assistants , and a former state department official in charge of dealing with Pyongyang authorities .
the delegation 's nuclear expert is Hector , who led the united states ' los Salamos national laboratory , which pioneered the development of the atomic bomb , from 1985 to 1997 .
prior to this , north korea had recently informed the us embassy in beijing that Pyongyang was ready to attend the second round of six - party talks on the Korean peninsula nuclear crisis , which had been delayed .
US officials pointed out earlier this week that Pyongyang authorities had indicated their readiness to participate in the six - party talks held earlier this year .
at the conclusion of the first round of six - party talks held in beijing in august last year , north korea later criticized the talks as " useless . "
the second round of the six - party talks was originally scheduled to be held in december last year , but the talks were postponed until the beginning of this year because of differences in positions on the measures that must be taken to resolve the issue .
Washington demanded that north korea unilaterally abandon its nuclear weapons program , while Pyongyang insisted that the united states provide legally binding security assurances in exchange for abandoning its nuclear weapons development program .
the U.S. government says it has nothing to do with the U.S. delegation visiting North Korea
( Agence france - presse , washington , 2 nd ) - the us government said today that it has nothing to do with the two us delegations preparing to visit north korea in the hope of inspecting the Yongbyon nuclear power plant , which triggered diplomatic storms between the two countries .
at a time when china is trying to get the united states and north korea , as well as japan , russia and south korea , to return to the negotiating table , a delegation of us scholars and scientists and another delegation of us congressional assistants intends to visit north korea .
US State Department Deputy Spokesman Erelli said : &quot; we have nothing to do with this group or the plans these groups are rumored to be planning to visit North Korea . &quot;
" I think you should know for sure that these groups or individuals do not represent the government , " Erelli said .
one delegation , led by a senior chinese expert at Stanford university and a nuclear scientist and former director of the Losaramus laboratory , included us state department special envoy Pritchard for talks with north korea last year .
the delegation will visit the Yongbyon nuclear power plant , the us daily reported today , but a member of the delegation told afp that the trip to Yongbyon was still uncertain .
the visit is also likely to change after extensive media coverage , and it remains uncertain whether the delegation will be allowed to enter north korea .
the other delegation was led by assistant to the chairman of the senate foreign relations committee , Luis Ruggie , and assistant to Biden , senior democratic member of the senate foreign relations committee , ji haofeng .
