( Agence france - presse , washington , 2nd ) - the us government said today that Israel has not yet given a satisfactory answer to a us request for clarification of reports that Israel intends to expand Jewish settlement plans in the occupied golan heights .
the state department said that Israel had responded to the us request after the incident was reported on Wednesday ( 31 july ) .
however , Israel 's response did not fully clear the united states of its doubts .
State department deputy spokesman Erelli said : " we have received an answer , but it is not a clear answer , and we do not know the situation . "
he reiterated washington 's opposition to any new Israeli settlement activities .
Erelli said , &quot; We have made it clear that we are against the new settlement activities . we do not think it is beneficial . the settlement activities should be stopped . &quot;
according to media reports , Israel plans to add nine new settlements to the golan heights occupied by Syria in 1967 and increase the Jewish population from 10,500 to about 15,000 over a three - year period .
this occupation move has been widely criticized by many arab countries as illegal .
