Japanese geisha Yoshiharu Nakamura dies in new york at age 90
( Agence france - presse , Tokyo , july 7 ) - Japanese publisher Kushima news agency announced that Himura Nakamura , who had given up her career as a geisha and moved to the united states for nearly half a century , died in her new york home on the 5 th at the age of 90 .
the caosi society has published 10 works on Happy Spring in Nakamura , including Nakamura 's 1983 autobiographical bestseller " a generation of children of Edo . "
" a generation of Edo artistes " has been translated into eight languages and adapted into tv dramas and stage plays in the country . the book describes Himura Nakamura as the only Japanese geisha who could speak english before world war ii .
many foreign celebrities , including french avant - garde artist Shankotto , comedy leader Chaplin , and us baseball star BABE Ruth , were warmly received by Nakamura during their visit to Tokyo that year .
the caosi society said that Nakamura inspired shankokedo to write a poem , " artistes . "
Nakamura , born to a family of doctors in Tokyo 's Ginza high - class district , became a geisha in the Shinhashi entertainment district at the age of 16 , despite parental opposition , Kusashi said in a statement .
after many years as a geisha in xinqiao , Nakamura married a diplomat in 1940 and soon divorced .
after the war , Nakamura resumed her career as a geisha at xinqiao and immigrated to the united states in 1956 .
in addition to teaching traditional Japanese dance music in the united states , Nakamura also serves as an opera consultant , including lady butterfly .
Nakamura , who has a son , is currently a professor of modern art at the university .
Vietnam airlines opens new route to Frankfurt , Germany
( Agence france - presse , Hanoi , 8th ) - Vietnamese airlines have opened up a two - week flight to Frankfurt , Germany . this is Vietnam 's second flight point in europe after Paris , france , and is also part of Vietnam 's strategy of rapidly expanding its routes .
Vietnam airlines will use Boeing 767 passenger planes to take off from ho chi Minh city every Tuesday and Thursday , passing through Hanoi and Moscow to Frankfurt .
" we have opened this route to serve a large number of Vietnamese nationals residing in Germany , " a Vietnamese airline spokesman said .
Vietnam airlines , which currently has more than 20 international destinations , opened many new routes last year and plans to further expand them .
Vietnam airlines earlier this week announced plans to double its fleet to 70 by 2010 .
despite the outbreak of Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome ( SARS ) and the war in Iraq in 2003 , Vietnam Airlines &apos; passenger capacity increased by 1 per cent to 4.05 million .
Vietnam airlines has set a passenger loading target of 5 million this year , of which foreigners account for about half ( 2.4 million ) .
