( Agence france - presse , manila , 10th ) - the philippine military said that the communist rebels launched a new wave of rebel attacks , including raiding a power plant and setting fire to a telecommunications tower , killing eight people .
the attacks coincided with a statement issued by a spokesman for the New People &apos;s Army ( NPA ) of the Communist Party of the Philippines , which stated that it would no longer seek peace talks with Philippine President Arroyo &apos;s government and would await the appearance of a successor president .
" we no longer have any hope for peace talks with the Arroyo government , even though Arroyo said they were ready to talk , " new people 's army spokesman Rochard said in a televised interview .
the philippine government originally planned to hold preliminary discussions with the philippines communists later this month on resuming formal peace talks .
Rochard pointed out that the philippine communist party will ask the rival candidates in the Arroyo presidential election in may to put forward their suggestions on resuming peace talks after their election .
Rochard said that the philippine communist party is also prepared to request the removal of the black list of terrorist groups in the united states and europe as a precondition for resuming peace talks .
fifty philippine communist guerrillas attacked government troops in Karaja city power plant and garrison power plant , killing three government soldiers and four new people 's army guerrillas of the philippine communist party on the spot , and injuring seven other government soldiers .
