China sends delegation to us to purchase more than $ 2 billion worth of high - tech equipment
( Agence france - presse , beijing , 12th ) - according to official media reports , a chinese procurement delegation to the united states will sign several contracts to purchase more than $ 2 billion worth of high - tech equipment from us manufacturers .
quoting an official from the ministry of information industry , the beijing morning post said the contracts , which will be signed in the united states tomorrow , include Motorola semiconductor manufacturing company , Intel company , and Cisco systems company .
the chinese manufacturers participating in the contract are some of the major telecommunications and computer manufacturers , including china telecom group company and Lenovo group company .
this is the third chinese procurement mission to the united states since november last year .
the move is part of china 's ongoing efforts to reduce its growing trade surplus with the united states .
a us commerce official welcomed the move as it would help reduce the us trade deficit with china , the beijing morning post reported .
