US wants Asian countries to rid themselves of fear of mad cow disease
( Agence france - presse , manila , 14th ) - us agricultural officials said that despite a mad cow disease outbreak in the united states last month , Asian countries will soon be able to eat us beef at ease .
however , several Asian countries , including japan and south korea , immediately banned or restricted the import of us beef .
US officials said yesterday that the relevant units have expanded their investigation into mad cow disease and that beef from the original mad cow disease site has not been exported . in addition , the relevant units have been stepping up quarantine and strictly preventing explosive mad cow disease in the past 10 years .
mad cow disease , also known as bovine spongiform encephalopathy ( BSE ) , is associated with human spongiform encephalopathy ( Koujia &apos;s disease ) , which leads to vacuolation of the human brain .
" we are very optimistic that these Asian countries will further reduce the scope of the existing ban in the next month or so , " said green , director of the Asian affairs department of the us department of agriculture , at a press conference in manila .
green added : &quot; we have assured all Asian countries of the safety of US beef . &quot;
he said that the Japanese delegation is visiting the united states to learn on - the - spot about us measures to prevent mad cow disease .
