( Agence france - presse , Seoul , 14th ) - south Korean officials said south korea has stepped up quarantine work to curb the further spread of bird flu after nine days of no incident .
South korea 's agriculture ministry said an enhanced quarantine zone had been set up near a chicken farm in the Ryangsan area , 390 kilometers southeast of Seoul .
health officials detected the bird flu virus in the area on Monday .
this is the first confirmed case of avian influenza virus in south korea in nine days .
the highly contagious poultry disease is apparently under control after an outbreak of bird flu in 15 parts of south korea last month forced authorities to cull nearly two million chickens and ducks .
Kim Chang-seok , director of the animal health section of the south Korean ministry of health ( transliteration ) , said : " we cull all chickens in the epidemic area and strictly restrict the movement of these poultry . "
the emergence of new cases of bird flu has prompted south Korean government officials to step up quarantine in other areas .
Kim Chang - Suk said the bird flu virus can survive for two weeks in the dust and at least 35 days in poultry feces .
