( Agence france - presse , Wellington , 15th ) - according to the latest quarterly survey report released by the new zealand economic research center , despite the negative impact of the new zealand dollar 's rise , business circles remain deeply confident in new zealand .
the report pointed out that only 2 percent of companies were pessimistic about the business environment in the next six months , compared with 3 percent and 20 percent respectively in the first two quarters of this year .
the above - mentioned research center pointed out that according to various indicators of the survey report , there was solid economic growth in the fourth quarter of last year , with the activities of the business sector itself increasing by 31 percent .
however , according to the forward - looking indicators , new zealand 's economic growth can be expected to " continue to decline moderately in the next few quarters . "
the rapid appreciation of the new zealand dollar in the past three months has widened the confidence gap between exporters and non - exporters , said economist Jadina of the new zealand economic research center .
eleven per cent of manufacturing and construction exporters expect the outlook to deteriorate in the next six months , while another 14 per cent of non - exporters are optimistic about the outlook for the next six months .
the new zealand dollar has appreciated 30 percent in the past two years .
