Shinsei bank , formerly known as the japan long - term credit bank , was taken over by the state in 1998 after its bankruptcy , and the reformed shinsei bank has already provided retail financial services .
Shinsei bank expects net profit to reach 65 billion yen ( 613 million us dollars ) for the year ending march 2004 , up 22.6 percent from the previous year , recurrent interest to 60 billion yen , up 76.5 percent , and total revenue to 175 billion yen , down 13 percent .
