they said that this was done before iraq launched three attacks on us military helicopters this month , but the last three attacks will only confirm the findings of the study .
the main purpose of the military research report is to provide ways for us pilots to evade attacks by such weapons as Iraqi guerrillas , and relevant officials are reluctant to discuss the newly discovered contents .
however , judging from the method of the new wave of attacks in iraq , one cannot help but worry that the Iraqi guerrillas have carefully studied the combat mode of the us aircraft .
the researchers found that the Iraqi guerrillas had used the sa - 16 shoulder missile on more than one occasion , which was particularly worrying .
it is very difficult for pilots to avoid such missiles with precision navigation systems .
a senior us airman in the Persian gulf region said : " every time our plane is shot down , it is a great strategic victory for the enemy .
not only did the news spread wildly , but the winner and loser also made a verdict . therefore , the enemy thought this was a very useful trick . "
since october 25 last year , nine us helicopters have been shot down or fallen , killing at least 49 us troops .
