the boy died of illness at ho chi Minh city 's no. 2 children 's hospital on january 22 , the head of ho chi Minh city health bureau , Nguyen Duc Duan , told afp today .
he was sent to hospital on the 19 th with respiratory symptoms .
the who also said that it is currently following the development of the epidemic together with the Vietnamese authorities .
another Vietnamese health official pointed out that on the 22 nd , a sister died of a serious respiratory disease in a hospital in Hanoi , and health authorities suspected that the two were also victims of avian influenza .
millions of chickens suffer from bird flu in indonesia
( Agence france - presse , Jakarta , 25th ) - indonesia 's agriculture ministry announced today that the bird flu epidemic has killed millions of chickens , but so far there have been no cases of human infection .
no one in indonesia has been infected with the potentially deadly disease so far , said sudaga , director of the animal affairs department of the ministry of agriculture .
six people have died in Vietnam after bird flu outbreaks in seven countries in the Asian region .
Indonesian officials said earlier that bird flu , which was prevalent in poultry in java and Tahrir island last november , was Newcastle disease .
a spokesman for the ministry of agriculture said here today that there are no signs of bird flu in indonesia .
in the evening , he told Agence France-Presse that it was not clear whether the outbreak was caused by the H5N1 virus .
the majority of avian influenza deaths in Viet Nam have been caused by infection with the H5N1 virus .
the spokesman said that the new town disease , together with avian influenza type a , had killed 4.7 million poultry since november last year .
about 60 per cent of them died from Newcastle disease .
he said no immediate culling operation had been ordered .
the Indonesian state news agency quoted sudaga as saying that the authorities have used british and Australian sera to determine the type of virus , but the test results may not be available until Wednesday or Thursday , after which the government will submit a report to relevant international organizations .
snow covers northwestern europe causing major traffic and transport disruption
( Agence france - presse , Paris , 29th ) - the snowstorm covered most of western and northern europe , causing great traffic and railway chaos and forcing the cancellation of hundreds of flights in britain , Germany , and denmark .
in london , more than 200 flights were canceled last night as a result of snow cover , and 80 flights were canceled early this morning , an airport spokesman said .
two other airports near london , Gatwick and stansted , were also affected by snow and 18 flights were cancelled due to weather conditions .
in Germany , winter weather has led to the cancellation of at least 60 flights to Frankfurt international airport , the largest airport in Germany .
transport authorities said the departure of dozens of other flights to Frankfurt could affect air traffic throughout the day .
in france , road traffic restrictions were imposed in Paris after a snowfall last night , but similar measures in other parts of france were lifted this morning .
services at Paris 's main airport are reported to be close to normal , with delays at Charles de Gaulle airport due to snow and fog yesterday .
however , the Paris airport authorities advise passengers travelling by air to make sure that their flights take off and land on time before going out .
apart from the coast in the middle of the earth , most of france is covered with snow .
as both Taiwan and japan are democratic countries , they have an obligation and even greater responsibility to make joint efforts to consolidate democracy in asia .
in order to propagate democratic values , the chinese government will set up a " Taiwan democracy foundation " in the near future , of which international cooperation among political parties is one of the focal points .
the democratic progressive party hopes to join hands with democratic parties in various countries to share its experience in democratic development with other countries , to contribute to peace , stability , and prosperity in asia , and to realize the ideal of the " Asian democratic alliance " at an early date .
today , when the international situation is changing rapidly , the ups and downs of regional forces affect the whole body , and the security of all countries is put to the test .
as far as the asia - pacific region is concerned , since the united states launched a war against iraq last month , the nuclear - armed and self - respecting north korea has repeatedly tested missiles and overflew japan 's territorial airspace , and china has long actively expanded its armament and deployed ballistic missiles to target Taiwan .
all this has posed a serious threat to the security of Taiwan , japan , and the asia - pacific region .
these issues , which have a bearing on the consolidation of democracy and the maintenance of security , require formal security mechanisms to be discussed and resolved .
today 's meeting is the first formal dialogue on security issues between the democratic progressive party , Taiwan 's ruling party , and the ruling liberal democratic party of japan and members of other political parties . the importance of this is self - evident .
I also hope that in addition to the bilateral dialogues between Taiwan and japan , the united states , japan , south korea , and other neighboring countries in the asia - pacific region will be able to cooperate in promoting the establishment of a " security dialogue mechanism , " and support Taiwan 's participation in regional polygonal dialogue organizations to implement the spirit of " cooperative security . "
today is an important moment to inspire us to continue on the road of reform , and we affirm to the greatest extent that all comrades within the party can embody the will of the party and work together to realize the reform goals .
" withdrawal of a political party from the radio and television media " is the most basic requirement for implementing media reform . it is also an idea that the democratic progressive party has always adhered to . ruling the country will only accelerate the pace of reform , not obstruct or burden it .
we also know that in order to promote this goal , it is a small step , but also a crucial step , for the comrades in the party and public office within the party to be the first to withdraw from media operations .
in the era of media monopoly during the martial law period , many comrades in the party successively threw themselves into the arduous task of setting up a fourth station and a local radio station in order to strive for an open space for public opinion . through this method , they hoped to break through existing restrictions and increase the driving force for the transformation of the media environment .
for example , comrade Tsai tongrong put a lot of effort into the birth of the fourth wireless television station in those years and finally gave birth to " popular television . "
this move has a considerable impact on the overall media environment , especially breaking the long - term monopoly of the three stations and creating more space for cable television stations to develop .
however , we must understand that because of the limitations of the historical environment , there are many things that cannot be otherwise done in the process of promoting reform . therefore , today , when the media space is fully open and free , the tasks representing the stage have been accomplished , and in order for the reform process to continue , there must be sacrifices and sacrifices .
the standing committee of the CPC central committee announced that all comrades in public office of the party will withdraw from the operation of the radio and television media before the next session of the legislative yuan , that is , before 5 september , in order to set an example to fulfill their commitments to the people .
we are very pleased that all comrades who have taken the party 's ideals and goals as their thinking , including Cai tongrong , Zhang junhong , zhou qingyu , Hou shuisheng , Gao mengding , Huang naihui , and shen minggong , who have made great contributions to the democratic movement , have been able to abandon their egos and put emphasis on promoting media reform .
ruling is not the enjoyment of power , but an increase in responsibility .
in the course of taking office , the democratic progressive party may suffer setbacks and bumps . we can always turn challenges into momentum for progress , steadily lead Taiwan to construct a project of deepening democracy , and at the same time link up with the universal values of global democracy , peace , and prosperity .
this is because we always believe that the people are the masters of this country , and the responsibility of the democratic progressive party is to elevate the founding spirit of " being honest , diligent , and loving the native land " to a bright vision of " reform , progress , and a good life , " and to lay the foundation for lasting peace and stability for the 23 million Taiwanese .
for a long time , the democratic progressive party has played the role of " separate government " in its efforts to expand Taiwan 's foreign relations , creating brilliant results .
despite the continuous suppression by the chinese communists , we have never retreated , because our destiny is in our own hands . even without abundant resources , the democratic progressive party has made one step at a time and expanded the space for Taiwan 's international participation .
" pluralistic diplomacy " is the main axis of the overall foreign policy strategy of the democratic progressive party . over the past year , using the " Asian liberal democratic alliance " as a platform , we have successfully shared our experiences and exchanged views with political parties in the region on economic challenges , democratic reform of political parties , the elimination of money politics , the resolution of globalization and poverty , political propaganda and communication , and youth participation in politics .
in march next year , i will formally take over the chairmanship of the " alliance for freedom and democracy in asia , " hoping to create more opportunities for Taiwan to contribute to the international community as the leader of an international organization .
in addition , the Democratic Progressive Party has also actively participated in relevant meetings since it became a full member of the &quot; International Freedom League &quot; last year .
in addition to serving as the human rights commissioner in the secretariat of the london headquarters , he will also hold seminars on political reforms in central and south america , europe , and other places in cooperation with other member political parties .
on september 28 , our party celebrated its 17 th birthday .
along the way , the 17 - year - old democratic progressive party has always adhered to democratic ideals and is full of forces for reform and progress .
because we have always been on the side of democratic reform , we can win the trust of the Taiwan people , and because of this , the responsibilities and missions that we will shoulder in the future will be more serious and important .
when we took over as the ruling party three years ago , the previous ruling party had already gone through six roundabout constitutional amendments in the 1990 s .
the series of twists and turns in the process of amending the constitution from handling the general election of the national assembly in 1991 , the direct presidential election in 1994 , the freezing of provincial government organizations in 1997 , and the establishment of the national assembly in 2000 are , in fact , the trajectory of the Taiwan people in strengthening sovereignty and democratic legitimacy .
if we regard the direct election of the president in 1996 as the most important symbol for Taiwan to become a sovereign and independent democratic country , then by 2006 this " complete " country will be 10 years old .
after 10 years of practice , we must think about what we want to pursue next as a democratic country with independent sovereignty .
I must say that in the next stage , we should further pursue the deepening of democracy and a more efficient constitutional system in order to lead the Taiwan people to accept the grim challenges of the new century .
Asia is the world 's largest continent , with an area of nearly 30 percent of the world 's land mass . at present , its population accounts for 60 percent of the world 's total population and one - fourth of the world 's total economy . it should and can make outstanding contributions to world peace and development .
Asia has a long and splendid culture . the Yellow and Yangtze river basins , the Indus and Ganges basins , the Euphrates and the Tigris basins are famous birthplaces of human civilization .
in the long historical process , the Asian people have written a brilliant chapter for the development of human civilization .
in modern times , asia has endured vicissitudes of life and repeated hardships , and the people of all countries have made unremitting efforts and made tremendous achievements in striving for liberation and development .
however , there is still a long way to go to realize asia 's new rise and rejuvenation .
strengthening cooperation , promoting development , and achieving a win - win situation are the only way for asia to rise and rejuvenate , and are also where the fundamental interests of the Asian people lie .
under the new century and new situation , asia 's development is facing new opportunities .
peace and development are still the main themes of our times , and the overall peaceful international environment has provided favorable external conditions for asia 's development .
the in - depth development of economic globalization , the rapid progress of the world scientific and technological revolution , and the accelerated optimization and reorganization of international production factors and industrial transfer are conducive to the utilization of international capital by Asian countries , the introduction of advanced technology , the opening up of international markets , and the promotion of their own economic development .
Asia is rich in resources and has a vast market . it is the most economically dynamic region in the world today , with great potential for development .
large numbers of people and underdevelopment are the two major national conditions of china .
China has a population of 1.3 billion . no matter how small the problem is , multiplying by 1.3 billion will become a very big problem , and no matter how considerable the financial and material resources are , dividing by 1.3 billion , it will become a very low , very low per capita level .
this is something that chinese leaders must always remember .
we cannot rely on others to solve the problems of 1.3 billion people , we can only rely on ourselves .
since the founding of the people 's republic of china , great achievements have been made in our construction , and at the same time we have taken some detours and lost some opportunities .
since 1978 , when reform and opening up began , we have finally found a correct way to develop ourselves .
this is : the chinese people are building socialism with chinese characteristics independently .
the essence of this road is to mobilize all positive factors , liberate and develop productive forces , and respect and safeguard the chinese people 's freedom to pursue happiness .
China 's reform and opening up extends from the rural areas to the cities , from the economic field to the political , cultural , and social fields .
in the final analysis , every step it takes is aimed at letting the vitality of all labor , knowledge , technology , management , and capital burst forth one after another and allowing all sources of creating social wealth to flow in full .
in recent years , profound changes have taken place in the world , science and technology have changed with each passing day , the level of world productive forces has been constantly raised , and the world market has become more closely linked , thus opening up a historic opportunity for the development of various countries .
however , it is worth noting that power politics , regional conflicts , terrorism , infectious diseases , and environmental degradation are still threatening world stability and development .
the negative impact of economic globalization has increased the risks and costs of economic and social development in developing countries , and some developing countries are even in danger of being marginalized .
at present , despite the gradual recovery of the world economy , many uncertainties remain .
the doha round of multilateral trade talks has suffered setbacks and complicated factors such as trade protectionism have added to the difficulties of developing countries .
what is gratifying is that the vast number of developing countries have been forging ahead , are keen to reform , and are striving to rule the country , and have made remarkable achievements .
on the international stage , with the support of the non - aligned movement and the group of 77 , developing countries have strengthened unity and cooperation , made important contributions to safeguarding their own legitimate rights and interests and changing the irrational international political and economic order , and have become an important force in promoting the democratization of international relations .
at the same time , exchanges and cooperation among developing countries have also yielded fruitful results , and economic exchanges between them have become more frequent .
from the Andean mountains to the banks of the Mekong river , from the establishment of the Maghreb union to the establishment of the african union , south - south cooperation has been constantly enriched , perfected and updated from content to form , from mechanisms to means .
the past year was also a year in which sino - Canadian friendly and cooperative relations continued to develop in an all - round way .
trade between the two countries has maintained the momentum of growth , with the total volume of trade approaching $ 10 billion .
there have been frequent high - level exchanges . Canadian foreign ministers , defense ministers , environment ministers , and international cooperation ministers have visited china one after another . Chinese supreme court presidents , commerce ministers , and other high - ranking officials have also visited canada one after another . more importantly , the two prime ministers have successfully exchanged visits .
Premier Wen Jiabao 's recent visit to canada is of the significance of inheriting the past and forging ahead into the future , injecting new vitality into the further development of sino - Canadian relations , and laying a solid foundation for the continuous expansion and in - depth development of friendly cooperation between the two countries in various fields .
China and canada will continue to strengthen cooperation in the political , economic , cultural , educational , scientific , and technological fields and strive to achieve the goal of doubling the total volume of bilateral trade by 2010 .
dear overseas chinese and friends ,
although you live abroad , you have always been concerned about your hometown and the development of the motherland . at every crucial moment , you always worry about the worries of the people of the motherland , enjoy the happiness of the people of the motherland , and keep pace with the pulse of the motherland .
last year , after some areas of china were hit by sars and floods , you expressed your deep concern and blessings to the people of the motherland through the internet , letters , telephone calls , donations , and other means . Chinese from all walks of life also held a series of large - scale fundraising and charity shows one after another . after the successful manned space flight of Shenzhou v , your congratulatory telegrams , congratulatory letters , and greeting cards arrived one after another . all of you felt elated and proud of china 's achievements in space science and technology .
during premier Wen Jiabao 's visit to canada , hundreds of overseas chinese and foreign students braved the severe wind and rain and went to the airport and capitol hill to welcome premier Wen Jiabao . many moving scenes took place .
here , i would like to take this opportunity to express my heartfelt thanks to all of you . I believe that you will continue to make new and greater contributions to china 's prosperity and strength , the development of sino - Canadian relations , and china 's complete reunification and all - round revitalization in the new year .
first , strengthen political mutual trust and deepen strategic cooperation .
as permanent members of the un security council , china and france are countries with important influence on international affairs .
our two countries are in favor of promoting world multipolarization , advocating safeguarding the authority of the united nations , and are willing to promote the establishment of a new international political and economic order that conforms to the wishes of the peoples of all countries .
the two countries share broad consensus and common interests in dealing with various challenges facing mankind and in properly handling major international affairs .
we are willing to strengthen dialogue and consultations with france on major issues such as opposing terrorism , preventing proliferation , cracking down on transnational crimes , promoting common development , and strengthening the role of the united nations , to conduct close cooperation , and to strive to safeguard world peace and promote common development .
second , economic and trade cooperation should be strengthened to achieve mutual benefit and complementarity .
as the largest developing country in the world , china is making all - out efforts to modernize itself and has a vast market .
France is a developed country with an advanced level of economy and science and technology in the world , and has advanced technology in many fields .
the economies of our two countries are highly complementary and there is great potential for economic and trade cooperation .
since the founding of new china , the chinese government has always attached great importance to developing relations with africa and formulated a series of principles and policies .
we have always adhered to the five principles of peaceful coexistence , respected african countries ' independent choice of political systems and development paths , provided assistance to african countries to the best of our ability , and carried out economic and technological cooperation , supported african countries ' unity and cooperation to strengthen themselves , urged the international community to attach importance to peace and development in africa , supported african countries ' equal participation in international affairs , and strengthened consultations and cooperation between china and africa to jointly safeguard the rights and interests of developing countries .
China-Africa friendship has a long history and is deeply rooted in the hearts of the people .
since the founding of new china , we have always firmly supported africa 's national liberation cause and sincerely assisted african countries in developing their national economies .
the chinese experts , doctors , teachers , and workers sent to africa work side by side with the local people , enjoy friendly relations , and are like brothers and sisters .
in international affairs , china and african countries understand and support each other and have become trusted partners .
the chinese people will never forget that at the 26 th un general assembly in 1971 , with the vigorous support of the vast number of developing countries , including african countries , china successfully restored its legitimate seat in the united nations .
in recent years , personnel at all levels and in all quarters of china and africa have continuously deepened mutual political trust , economic and trade cooperation has yielded fruitful results , and friendly exchanges in the fields of culture and education , public health , science and technology , and sports have flourished . the sino - african cooperation forum , established at the beginning of the century , has established a new platform for developing sino - african relations and deepening cooperation .
China and africa have decided to establish a new - type partnership characterized by long - term stability , equality , and mutual benefit , and sino - african friendly cooperation has entered a new stage of all - round development .
seven years after Nixon 's visit to china and the publication of the sino - us Shanghai communique , the Carter administration accepted china 's stance on the Taiwan issue and established sino - us diplomatic relations .
this incident and Deng Xiaoping 's successful visit to the united states opened a new chapter in sino - us relations .
in the early days of Reagan 's administration , china and the united states had fierce confrontations on the Taiwan issue .
after arduous negotiations , the governments of the two countries issued a well - known communique in 1982 to reach an agreement on a step - by - step solution to the issue of arms sales to Taiwan .
the Shanghai communiqu , the sino - us communiqu on the establishment of diplomatic relations , and the ta ba tan 17 communiqu together constitute the political cornerstone of sino - us relations .
in the 10 years since the establishment of diplomatic relations , despite frequent struggles between the two countries on the Taiwan issue and other issues , sino - us relations have been generally stable , and exchanges and cooperation in various fields have been increasing day by day .
in the 1980 s and early 1990 s , there were drastic changes in eastern europe , the disintegration of the soviet union , the end of the cold war , and the most profound changes in the international situation since world war ii .
the united states has taken the lead in sanctioning china , announcing the sale of 150 f - 16 fighters to Taiwan , linking the human rights issue to the most favored nation status , and allowing lee Teng - hui to visit the united states , thus plunging sino - us relations into a low ebb .
with the rapid development of china 's economy , china 's international status has been continuously enhanced .
more and more people in the united states have come to realize that the improvement and development of sino - us relations is in the interests of the united states and china .
six months ago , in this very hall , we successfully launched the six - party talks process and set the direction for the peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue .
over the past six months , various parties have conducted uninterrupted dialogue and consultations , made extensive and in - depth preparations for holding a new round of talks , and enhanced mutual understanding of each other 's positions through this process .
at present , all sides are looking forward to discussing substantive issues and achieving concrete results in the second round of talks , agreeing to resolve each other 's concerns through coordinated and consistent steps , and hoping that the peace process pioneered by the six - party talks will be maintained .
these constitute an important basis for our talks today .
the important significance of the second round of talks lies in launching discussions on substantive issues , which marks another step forward in the peace talks process .
the current round of talks will involve establishing specific objectives for resolving the nuclear issue , exploring the first - phase measures for resolving the nuclear issue , and studying ways to continue the process of talks .
as the talks deepen , we will still have to cope with more difficulties and meet more challenges . however , this is precisely the responsibility entrusted to us by history and the expectation placed on us by the international community .
the fact that the six of us are gathered here represents the strong political desire of the governments and peoples of the six countries to seek peace .
the purpose of our talks is to expand consensus , not to highlight differences , and to resolve problems , not to intensify contradictions .
the chinese side believes that all parties concerned can realize their peace mission , show mutual respect , show flexibility , and narrow the gap with a constructive attitude and in the spirit of cooperation and understanding .
the second round of the six - party talks in beijing completed its scheduled agenda after more than three days of consultations .
I would like to thank the governments of various countries , as well as the heads of state , representatives , and working personnel , for their contributions to this work .
if it is said that the first round of talks has set the general goal of realizing the denuclearization of the peninsula , then the significance of this round of talks lies in holding substantive dialogues and taking a new step toward the realization of the general goal .
during the talks , all parties had in - depth and constructive discussions , explored ways and means of solving problems with wisdom and rationality , put forward valuable ideas , and made positive policy pronouncements .
the talks have yielded a series of useful results , especially the consensus reached on the next round of talks and the establishment of a working group , which is of great significance to advancing the peace talks process .
dear colleagues , peace and development are the themes of our great times .
the people of the six countries represented here need peace , yearn for peace , and love peace , and the people of all countries in the world need peace , yearn for peace , and love peace .
over the past three days , the international community has been watching beijing and Diaoyutai , placing high hopes on this round of talks .
perhaps some people will think that the results of the talks are not enough and the process is not fast enough .
in my opinion , the current round of talks was launched against a backdrop of a lack of mutual trust among the parties concerned and a widening gap in their positions .
the chinese government 's stand on the Taiwan issue is consistent , that is , it adheres to the basic principle of peaceful reunification and one country , two systems .
to this end , we have made every effort to show the greatest sincerity and done a lot of work .
however , our efforts have been provoked by the Taiwan authorities and the pro - Taiwan independence forces .
we respect the democratic demands of the Taiwan people , but we oppose the Taiwan authorities and the pro - Taiwan independence forces from engaging in pro - Taiwan independence activities under the pretext of democracy to separate Taiwan from the motherland .
the reason why we have clearly expressed our determination and will to safeguard the reunification of the motherland is to safeguard peace and stability in the Taiwan strait region .
we have indicated that as long as there is a glimmer of hope , we will do our utmost to realize the motherland 's reunification by peaceful means .
we appreciate that president bush once again reiterated his adherence to the one - china stand and sent a clear signal to the pro - Taiwan independence forces .
the leader of the Taiwan authorities claimed that in order to prevent china from invading Taiwan by force and unilaterally change the cross - strait status quo , it is necessary to promote a peaceful referendum on 20 march .
this is a slander against the mainland 's peace efforts and a provocation against cross - strait relations .
at present , the real threat to Taiwan 's security does not come from the mainland , but from the Taiwan authorities ' wanton separatist activities in support of Taiwan independence .
it is the separatist forces advocating Taiwan independence that are directly responsible for undermining the current situation of cross - strait relations and endangering peace in the Taiwan strait .
the Taiwan authorities distorted the mainland 's opposition to Taiwan independence and the maintenance of stability in the Taiwan strait as suppressing Taiwan 's democracy and freedom , and used this as an excuse to launch a referendum .
this is groundless and perverting right and wrong , and is to gain sympathy and support for his continued pursuit of the separatist line .
the leader of the Taiwan authorities claims that what he will hold is a so - called defensive referendum and a peaceful referendum , but no matter how it is packaged , such a provocative act will only provoke confrontation and hostility between the two sides of the strait , aggravate cross - strait tension , and push cross - strait relations to the brink of danger step by step .
this runs completely counter to the mainstream popular will of the Taiwan compatriots seeking peace , stability , and development . it is not the deepening of democracy in Taiwan . it is a misleading and manipulative act against the Taiwan people . it is also a serious threat to peace and stability in the asia - pacific region . it is bound to be universally opposed by compatriots on both sides of the strait and the international community .
taking a panoramic view of the historical process of the development of the chinese nation , reunification has always been the mainstream , the trend of the times , and the aspiration of the people .
with the growing strength of the motherland and the continuous strengthening of cross - strait cooperation , the international community has generally recognized the consolidation of the one - china pattern , and any separatist plot is doomed to failure .
the lunar new year is still more than two weeks away and is one of the traditional festivals to which the chinese people attach great importance .
on this joyous day , we used to get together with our close relatives and friends and exchange gifts as a token of our appreciation .
in the spirit of " connecting people and delivering business opportunities , " Hongkong post has partnered with china post to launch the " Hong kong / mainland gift fulfillment service " to deliver the greetings and blessings of Hong kong people to their relatives , friends and customers living in the mainland or Hong kong during the spring festival .
Hongkong post has always been committed to co - operating with other postal administrations in providing international logistics services .
as early as december 2002 , the company launched a foreign wine logistics service with australia post to provide quality products to the people of Hong kong .
in our cooperation with china post , we have extended our close co - operation in postal services , postal remittance services and express delivery services to cross - boundary logistics services to cater for the increasing market demand for gifts from Hong kong people to relatives , friends or customers in the mainland .
the first batch of gifts consisted of a number of beautifully packaged lunar new year gift boxes containing festive sweets , tea leaves and seafood .
it is a most respectable gift to friends and relatives in the mainland and business partners alike .
over the past 30 years , the consumer council has made a remarkable contribution to consumer protection .
the best way to evaluate the effectiveness of the council 's work is to see if there has been any substantial improvement in consumer rights and interests .
I agree with chairman Chen that over the past 30 years , not only consumers are aware of their rights and interests , but all sectors of the community also attach importance to consumers ' rights and interests , and this is the result of the efforts of the consumer council and the government .
the council conducts regular product testing , market research on different products and services , and studies the operation of the industry , and disseminates fair and objective market information to the public through the monthly magazine Choice .
the " choice " monthly magazine is deeply trusted by the public . now that the " choice " monthly magazine has developed an online version , it will give more effective play to its functions and help consumers more easily and quickly acquire market information .
the council operates 11 district consumer enquiry centres and 16 telephone hotlines to provide consumers with information on goods and services and to receive complaints from consumers .
since its establishment , the number of enquiries received by the council has increased steadily , from thousands at the beginning of the 1970 s to 146,000 last year , a more than 20 - fold increase , indicating that more and more consumers will take account of the council 's reports and comments before making their choice of products and services .
in addition , the council handled more than 26,000 complaints this year .
the council will also identify individual shops operating under unscrupulous practices , which will not only help consumers guard against deception , but will also serve as a deterrent to operators .
