in this regard , in the past six to seven months , the government and i have been working hard to improve the situation . seeing that the citizens ' demand is to do a good job in the economy and the people 's livelihood , we have also made a lot of efforts in this regard . we also know that the citizens have many opinions on article 23 of the basic law . we have withdrawn article 23 . in fact , the government has made an immediate response .
I am also fully aware of the democratic aspirations of the community .
but , Hon Yeoh , i would like to tell you that what i am doing today is to make sure that everything goes smoothly after the constitutional review begins , so there are some fundamental issues that need to be addressed first . these are two different things .
what is the basic question ?
some are problems of principle and some are problems of law , which have a bearing on the relevant regulations of the constitutional review of the basic law . how to understand them is to do a good job in this respect first .
we are doing this part of our work and a three - member group has already started to do so .
it will consult the central authorities and listen to your views in Hong kong , which i think is a good step and a decision we have made to take seriously the views of the Hong kong community .
in today &apos;s competitive business environment , brands play a key role in the success of products .
the creation of brand names cannot be achieved overnight , but requires creative design , excellent quality , thoughtful packaging , effective marketing and sustained investment .
Hong kong has the conditions to create brand names .
we have the relevant knowledge , skills and experience , talented people in everything from design , manufacturing and marketing to management , and we have a vast market .
the CEPA , which has just begun to be implemented , will increase our advantages . in addition to the zero tariff preference for entering the mainland market , its greatest advantage is to encourage businessmen to think more and strive to increase the added value of their products , so that they will become brand names loved by consumers in Hong kong , the mainland , and even the whole world .
the chinese manufacturers ' association 's " Hong kong top ten brand competitions " coincided with the CEPA 's drive to develop Hong kong 's products in a high value - added direction .
in the past five years , the election has produced 51 " top ten brand names in Hong kong . "
however , faced with this huge market in the mainland , 51 brand names are really nothing . we need hundreds , thousands , and more " Hong kong brand names . "
over the years , the MTR has actively participated in MTR projects in major mainland cities , bringing their rich experience in Hong kong to the mainland market through service delivery .
I am very pleased that the quality of Hong kong 's investment , professional services and management staff has been recognised in the domestic market .
