a few days ago , the provisional Iraqi governing council and the us occupation authorities signed an agreement in Baghdad announcing a step - by - step timetable for the return of power to iraq by june next year .
the agreement was reluctantly endorsed by the international community : although the eu foreign ministers ' meeting welcomed it , france considered the process too slow , un secretary general Kofi Annan , while encouraged by the power transfer plan , said the time was not ripe for the united nations to play a role in iraq , and russia simply questioned the legitimacy of the agreement .
the Iraqi people 's reaction was lukewarm , and us public opinion even considered it a major gamble .
in short , people tend to be skeptical and wait and see .
there is reason for the international community to be sceptical .
this is because people see that returning to iraq is not a willful move of the united states . therefore , the transfer of power is unlikely to be complete , and there are bound to be many foreshadows .
the first is that the interim transitional government to be formed in may next year is not directly elected by the Iraqi people , but by a transitional national congress elected by 18 provincial election committees .
this makes it difficult to avoid suspicion of being manipulated by the united states , and its legitimacy may be questioned .
second , the united states has announced that after the handover of power , the united states will not withdraw its troops , and will only turn its original military occupation into a = military presence .
the us government announced on 18 november that it has decided to impose quota restrictions on the import of knitted fabrics , corsets , and robes from china .
at a time when china is constantly striving to expand economic and trade cooperation between china and the united states , the us government 's protectionist measures cannot but deeply regret this .
with the development of economic globalization to today , it is extremely inappropriate for the united states to reimpose restrictions on china 's textile imports .
first of all , this abuse of the quota limit limits the implementation of the wto 's principle of free trade .
is it too arbitrary and unfair to talk about free trade in a high - sounding manner on the one hand , and to put up new trade barriers at the same time ?
second , the quota limit has restricted the sound development momentum of sino - us economic and trade relations .
since china and the united states reached an agreement on china 's accession to the wto in 1999 , us exports to china have grown at an average annual rate of 15 percent .
in january and september this year , us exports to china rose 26.2 percent year - on - year .
in the past two years , us exports of textile raw materials and manufactured goods to china have increased by a big margin .
as a matter of fact , china today has become the country with the fastest growth in us exports to other countries in the world .
there are many reasons why bush 's visit to britain failed to achieve his goal . the most important reason is that after the end of the cold war , the united states became the only superpower in the world , ignoring others and expanding unilateralism .
without the authorization of the united nations , the united states launched a war against iraq and did not respect the opinions of its major allies on major international issues such as iraq 's reconstruction . we have always violated public anger .
according to an opinion poll recently released by the european commission , 68% of eu citizens believe that the united states has insufficient reasons to launch the iraq war , and 53% believe that the united states constitutes a threat to world peace .
second , the united states stresses anti - terrorism , asking allies to contribute funds , but ignores their concerns .
on the iraq reconstruction project , the united states is firmly in the palm of its hand , and the main contract for the first time was awarded to its own companies rather than taking a share of the profits . on the steel trade dispute , the world trade organization has already made a ruling , the united states imposed high tariffs and violated regulations , and the british industrial and commercial circles had hoped that bush would make concessions on this trip , but in the end they did not make a clear stand .
third , the united states regards its own values as the highest criterion above other countries , and wants to persist in carrying out democratic transformation of middle east countries , which has been criticized . some allies have demanded that the united states respect the culture and characteristics of islamic countries . they believe that one of the reasons why the us military is bogged down in the quagmire in iraq today is precisely the bitter result of its disrespect for other countries .
however , bush will not change course because of widespread criticism and opposition . during his visit , he once again defended his iraq policy and stressed that the us - british coalition forces will continue to use force to deal with violent incidents in iraq .
since bush 's current visit to britain did not go as planned , the situation in iraq will not necessarily develop as the white house hopes .
after six months of controversy , the advance party of japan 's self - defense forces finally set out for iraq before the end of 2003 .
this is the first time since the end of world war ii that japan has sent troops to overseas battlefields .
it reflects japan 's will to become a political and military power , and also marks the beginning of a change in japan 's defense strategy .
the reason why the SDF 's visit has attracted people 's attention is that it is not an isolated incident .
Japan used the war in afghanistan as an opportunity to achieve a breakthrough for the self-defense forces to go out of the country , used the Korean peninsula issue to pass an emergency rule of law , and laid the groundwork for the self-defense forces to use force or even pre-empt attacks . recently , the Koizumi cabinet adopted the " basic plan for supporting iraq 's reconstruction , " paving the way for sending troops to iraq .
step by step , they finally broke through the limitations of japan 's peace constitution and sent troops to overseas battlefields .
in addition , japan is also preparing to revise the " concept of basic defense forces " in 2004 in order to legalize and perpetuate overseas troop deployments , and is also planning to set up a permanent unit for overseas deployments that will not be formed on a temporary basis .
at the same time , the Japanese cabinet meeting also decided to start deploying the missile defense system in early 2004 on the pretext of the so - called " Asahara missile threat , " and to introduce the us - made standard sentry - 3 and sensu - 3 missiles to intercept missiles outside and re - entry into the atmosphere , respectively , so as to build a dual missile interception network .
it is not difficult to see that japan 's self - defense forces are moving in the direction of the regular army , which has both offensive and defensive capabilities , and the so - called Asahi Self - Defense Force , which specializes in guarding Taiwan , seems to be dying in name only .
the reason why japan 's actions have attracted people 's attention is first of all because these military decisions are an impact on japan 's peace constitution .
after paying homage to Yasukuni shrine , Koizumi gave an interview to Japanese reporters and defended his actions .
his arguments are self - contradictory and full of holes .
asked why Koizumi visited the shrine , Koizumi replied that japan 's peace and prosperity were realized on the basis of the victims of the war .
I have come to pray for peace and prosperity in Japan .
may i ask if Koizumi 's so - called victims of the war in Tae also include Hideki Tojo and other class - a war criminals of world war ii ?
can it be said that the realization of peace and prosperity in japan after world war ii also has the foundation contribution of class - a war criminals ?
a reporter asked : why did you choose to visit the Yasukuni shrine on 1 january ?
Koizumi said : it is a tradition in japan to pay homage to shrines on the first day of the new year . many people pay homage to shrines on this day .
it is understandable that ordinary people mourn for their relatives and friends . moreover , many of the bereaved families have made it clear that their visit to Yasukuni shrine is only to mourn their relatives and friends , and they resolutely oppose the Yasukuni shrine for worshipping class - a war criminals .
the chinese people are reasonable , and we have always insisted on distinguishing the Japanese people from a handful of militarists , separating the ordinary people from the right wing , and paying homage to Yasukuni shrine by the ordinary people is not the crux of the historical problem .
unity is strength .
this is an irrefutable truth .
to realize the grand goal of building a moderately prosperous society in an all - round way and accomplish the sacred cause of the great rejuvenation of the chinese nation , we must unite all forces that can be united .
the patriotic united front work and the CPPCC work in the new century and in the new stage must take this as the fundamental starting point and end - result .
we should further uphold and perfect the system of multi - party cooperation and political consultation under the leadership of the CPC , further consolidate and develop the patriotic united front , mobilize all positive factors to the fullest extent , and constantly add new strength to the great rejuvenation of the chinese nation .
in the past year , the CPPCC has firmly grasped the two main themes of unity and democracy , conscientiously performed all its functions , and played an important role in promoting china 's all - round economic and social development and safeguarding the overall situation of reform , development , and stability .
in the new year , it is hoped that the CPPCC will closely center on the central work of the party and the state , further do a good job in political consultation , democratic supervision , and participation in and discussion of state affairs , carry forward its fine traditions , give play to its own advantages , conduct in - depth investigations and studies , actively offer suggestions and suggestions , and make new and greater contributions to building a moderately prosperous society in an all - round way .
from 4 to 6 january , the 12th summit meeting of the south Asian association for regional cooperation ( SAARC ) was held in Islamabad , which was postponed for an entire year . the meeting approved the " framework treaty on south asia 's free trade agreement , " the " additional protocol to the SAARC convention on combating terrorism , " and the " south asia social charter , " among other documents , and announced that the SAARC countries will devote themselves to common development and cooperation in the economic , cultural , and anti-terrorism fields .
during the SAARC summit , the bilateral meeting between indian prime minister Vajpayee and Pakistani president Pervez Musharraf was particularly eye - catching .
at the last summit , Musharraf 's handshake with Vajpayee did not give people much hope for the development of bilateral relations .
two years later , due to a series of major measures taken by the two sides , such as restoring normal diplomatic relations , air and land communications , and realizing a cease - fire in Kashmir , india - Pakistan relations continued to ease up and finally took the opportunity of the SAARC summit to meet at the highest level .
the two countries have taken another big step forward in the process of improving bilateral relations , and regional cooperation in south asia is ushering in a new turn for the better .
although indian foreign minister Singha said on the 4 th that the meeting was held in a ceremonial manner , people believe that the meeting means that indian - Pakistani relations will continue to be adjusted in a more positive and pragmatic direction .
the leaders of the two countries have realized that tension and confrontation are not in the interests of the two countries , and on the contrary , opportunities for economic development have been lost time and again .
with the further development of economic globalization , strengthening cooperation and revitalizing the economy have become the top priorities of the governments of the two countries .
although the results of the presidential election held in georgia on 4 april have not yet been officially announced , the victory of the candidate jointly nominated by the right - wing political parties and leader of the national movement party , Saakashvili , has become a foregone conclusion .
Georgia 's central election commission announced today that more than 95 percent of voters support Sakashvili , according to a poll of 89 percent of the votes cast .
some cis heads of state also sent congratulatory messages to this young politician .
in fact , as early as the evening after the election , Sakashvili announced his victory .
he called the result a victory for the people of tajikistan and said georgia would act quickly to open up a new future .
in an interview with the news media , many voters said that voting for Sakashvili means choosing a new hope .
even former president Shevardnadze , who was forced to resign , expressed support for this former political enemy and praised him for being young , energetic , and well - educated .
while pinning hopes on Saakashvili , people have also noticed that the situation in georgia has not changed significantly in the past two months since Shevardnadze resigned .
it can be said that the newly elected president will still face the same old problems .
the past year has been an important but unusual one in china 's development process .
we have waged an extremely arduous struggle against the sudden outbreak of sars and scored major victories at this stage , maintained a good momentum of economic development , surpassed us $ 1,000 per capita gdp to a new level , successfully carried out the manned space flight Zhangzhou v , made the dream of the chinese nation 's flight to heaven a reality , and made national unity , social progress , and the people 's living standards further improved .
the achievements made in all aspects of our country have attracted worldwide attention , and the people throughout the country have paid great painstaking efforts to this end , displaying courage and strength in braving difficulties and dangers and creating miracles .
looking forward to the new year , we are full of confidence and hope .
taking a comprehensive look at the domestic and international situation , our country is in an important period of strategic opportunity in which we must grasp it tightly and can make great achievements .
we must persist in taking Deng Xiaoping theory and the important thinking of the " three represents " as our guide , comprehensively implement the spirit of the 16 th CPC national congress and the third plenary session of the 16 th CPC central committee , conscientiously implement the central committee 's major policy principles and overall arrangements for this year 's work , and continue to push forward reform , opening up , and modernization .
to do a good job in this year 's work , we must correctly grasp the situation . on the one hand , we must see favorable conditions and new opportunities , on the other hand , we must also see unfavorable conditions and new challenges , and enhance our sense of responsibility , urgency , and distress .
the three - party talks on the iraq issue were held at the un headquarters in new york on the 19 th . UN secretary general Kofi Annan held consultations with representatives of the Iraqi interim governing council and the us - british coalition provisional administration , focusing on how the united nations can play a role in iraq 's reconstruction .
the talks covered iraq 's politics , humanitarianism , security , and appointment of a un special representative in iraq . the three sides had a frank exchange of views on this .
the united states and britain are facing a boycott of their plan to transfer power in iraq . naturally , people are paying attention to whether and how the united nations will intervene in iraq 's reconstruction .
since the united states announced the end of the main war in iraq in early may last year , the situation in iraq has continued to be turbulent , and attacks against the occupation have occurred one after another , resulting in heavy casualties and almost no peace for the us - british coalition forces .
former Iraqi president Saddam was arrested on 13 december last year , but the joy of the united states did not last long , the security situation did not improve , and the intensification of the resistance movement put the occupation authorities in a predicament .
on the other hand , the Iraqi people and the arab countries unanimously demanded the withdrawal of foreign troops and the return of power to iraq so that the Iraqi people can run the country themselves .
at the same time , the united states and britain have striven to reshape the Iraqi regime according to their own will , and on this basis have gradually extricated themselves from the quagmire with dignity .
for this reason , the manner and process of transferring power has become the focus of current Iraqi affairs .
the idea of handing over power put forward by the us and british administrations and the Iraqi interim governing council in november last year is that the interim Iraqi transitional government formed before 1 july this year will be elected by the Tanabata transitional national congress , but the deputies attending the congress will be selected by the senegalese provincial election committee .
on the other hand , Shia , who constitute the majority of the Iraqi population , stressed that direct national general elections should be held in order to return to iraq in a truly fair manner .
US secretary of state Colin Powell 's recent visit to russia is still a focus of public opinion .
on the one hand , this is because the united states and russia are decisive , and their mutual relations have a far - reaching impact on the world today .
more importantly , Powell 's Moscow trip was full of substance and sent a clear signal : dark clouds have appeared in the sky of russian - us relations .
if these dark clouds do not dissipate in a timely manner , the prospects for bilateral relations may dim .
although the channels of dialogue between Washington and Moscow were very open , Powell decided to write an article in the influential Russian newspaper Izvestia to clarify his position .
Powell pointed out in the article that the united states has been puzzled by a series of events in russia 's internal and foreign affairs over the past few months .
he held that the russian regime has not yet completely accepted the restrictions of the law , and the key elements of civil society , such as freedom of the press and the development of political parties , are not strong enough .
Russia 's policy in Chechnya and its attitude toward its cis neighbors are even more worrying to the united states .
in the view of the diplomats , using the mass media to make public statements is the last way to communicate information .
the original intention of the united states in making this choice is thought - provoking , and it is obvious that russia is embarrassed and unhappy about it .
after entering the new century , economic globalization has become a major and grim challenge facing african countries .
African leaders are increasingly aware that africa can no longer afford to miss the opportunity and should rise to the occasion to find a response .
since the inauguration of the african union on 9 july 2002 , african countries have been actively promoting the new partnership for africa 's development ( NEPAD ) , striving to develop their economies and extricate themselves as early as possible from their disadvantageous position in economic globalization , while at the same time making great efforts to resolve the issue of armed conflicts in the city , which is a major obstacle to africa 's great cause of revitalization , in order to create an environment of unity , peace and stability .
at present , the overall situation in africa is becoming more relaxed , hot issues are noticeably cooling down , and various countries have increased their sense of urgency to end armed conflicts .
with the strong support of the united nations and the international community , influential regional organizations , regional powers , and well - known politicians in africa have taken active action to step up efforts to resolve regional conflicts and eliminate civil strife , and some conflicts and turbulence that have lasted for many years have basically been brought under control .
for example , the democratic republic of the congo ( DRC ) formed a government of national unity in june last year , Sao Tome and Principe peacefully resolved the coup crisis in july , the Liberian government and rebel forces signed a peace agreement in the Ghanaian capital Accra in august , the Sudanese government and southern rebel forces began key talks to break the deadlock in the peace process in september , various Somali armed forces and political factions started peace talks in Kenya in october to discuss the national peace process , and the burundi government and rebel forces signed a peace agreement in november .
of course , the current stability situation in the african region is still relatively fragile , the gains in peace still need to be consolidated , and some potential or real armed conflicts have yet to be finally resolved .
at the same time , there is still a big gap between the economic growth rate of african countries and that of developing countries in asia and other regions , all of which are unfavorable factors for africa 's development .
how to effectively cope with the challenges of economic globalization and realize the dream of african renaissance still requires the african people to make long - term and arduous efforts .
recently , a succession of highly pathogenic avian flu outbreaks have occurred in some parts of our country .
the party central committee and the state council attached great importance to this issue , promptly made a series of major policy decisions , and explicitly put forward guiding principles and policy measures for prevention and control work .
all relevant localities and departments have taken urgent action to go all out to prevent the spread of the epidemic in accordance with the arrangements made by the party central committee and the state council .
at present , the work of preventing and controlling avian flu throughout the country is proceeding in an intense and orderly manner .
the highly pathogenic avian flu is a kind of animal epidemic disease that spreads quickly and causes great harm . it seriously endangers animal husbandry production and seriously endangers the health and safety of the people .
conscientiously doing a good job in preventing and controlling highly pathogenic avian influenza has a bearing on the health and safety of the masses , on agricultural development and on increasing peasants ' incomes , on the overall situation of economic development , and on social stability . all localities and departments should take the important thinking of the " three represents " as their guide , strengthen leadership , closely cooperate with each other , rely on scientific and legal prevention and control , mass control and resolute handling , earnestly implement all prevention and control measures in a spirit of being highly responsible to the people , and resolutely fight the battle against avian flu .
as the world 's largest debtor country , the united states ' foreign debt is increasing again .
the us treasury department announced on january 16 that by the end of september last year , the total amount of us debt to foreign creditors had reached $ 6.494 trillion , 2.2 percent higher than the previous figure .
on average , every american is already in debt of more than $ 20,000 .
coincidentally , a study published by the international monetary fund ( imf ) last week sounded a systematic and sharp alarm about the us financial base and pointed out that the record - breaking us foreign debt has reached a level that threatens global financial stability .
statistics show that foreign private investors control about 40% of us government bonds .
this is reminiscent of what Keynes suggested to president Roosevelt in the first half of the 20th century : adopting a deficit policy to stimulate the economy domestically , and solving the fiscal deficit through borrowing from abroad .
this move has indeed played an important role in stimulating effective demand and solving the pressing needs of the economic crisis .
however , people have seen that many us administrations have tended to use this as a panacea .
however , since president Reagan advocated tax cuts and military expansion in the 1980 s , the us fiscal deficit has gradually increased and has eventually become the largest debtor country .
the convening of the first round of six - party talks is an important step in the process of dialogue and peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula .
some common points formed by all parties during the talks have laid the necessary foundation for the continuation of the talks and further clarified the objectives , ways , and principles for resolving the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula .
over the past few months , all parties concerned have insisted on peacefully resolving the nuclear issue on the peninsula through dialogue , conducted extensive coordination and consultations at different levels on the basis of the results of the first round of six - party talks , and made unremitting efforts to hold the second round of talks as soon as possible .
at the same time , the DPRK and the united states have further shown varying degrees of flexibility .
at present , important progress has been made in the preparations for the talks , and it is expected that the talks will be held well .
whether or not the second round of the six - party talks can achieve results and sustain the peace talks process is of general concern to the parties concerned and the international community .
in response , a chinese foreign ministry spokesman said : the goal of the six - party talks is to maintain and promote the process of dialogue and peaceful settlement , and we are willing to make joint efforts with all parties to this end .
the chinese side 's basic starting point is to safeguard peace and stability on the Korean peninsula and realize the denuclearization of the peninsula .
the chinese side believes that so long as all parties present at the meeting uphold the sincerity of peace talks , respect each other , and hold consultations on an equal footing , they will be able to create favorable conditions for promoting the settlement of relevant issues .
at the end of the 1970 s , us - Libyan relations deteriorated and the two countries severed diplomatic ties in 1981 .
US president Reagan listed a long list of crimes for Libyan leader Gaddafi , such as accusing him of secretly developing nuclear weapons , engaging in foreign military intervention , and terrorism .
from verbal confrontation to military confrontation between the two sides , the united states launched two surgical air strikes against libya , namely , the Asahi steppes and the guangjin gorge .
since then , the united states has imposed economic sanctions on libya , carried out political strikes , contained it diplomatically , and threatened it militarily .
Gaddafi , under heavy pressure , did not give in .
at present , relations between the united states and libya are warming up , and some people attribute this entirely to the deterrent effect of the iraq war , which seems to be biased .
as a matter of fact , for many years , Gaddafi , who has a unique character , has been fighting against the united states on the one hand and throwing olive branches to the united states on the other , but unfortunately he has not received a response .
after the iraq war , all parties in the middle east readjusted their strategies and regrouped their regional forces , thus providing an opportunity for the united states and libya to resume diplomatic relations .
as far as Gaddafi is concerned , rapprochement with the united states can put an end to sanctions , revitalize the economy , improve the people 's livelihood , get out of an isolated situation , and merge into the international community .
Li gave up those things that he had not yet obtained and could not get at the moment in exchange for a new environment in another village with a bright future .
from 7 to 8 february , dignitaries from europe , the united states , and other regions of the world gathered in Munich , Germany , to attend the 40 th Munich security policy conference .
the so - called Munich security policy conference is a forum on international security issues founded by unofficial figures in Germany and subsidized by the german government . in recent years , especially after the 9 / 11 roundup , people have paid more and more attention to it , and it has been hailed as the ZhanDavos forum in the security field .
an important topic of the meeting was transatlantic relations .
the remarks made by the european and us political leaders at the meeting indicated that the two sides are working hard to shake off the shadow of the iraq war on bilateral relations and are trying to return to the track of cooperation .
Bertram , director of the Berlin institute for international and security affairs , said : this is a meeting between europe and the united states to mend their relations , and both sides have the desire to get closer again .
as far as european - us relations are concerned , the new message emanating from the meeting is that europe and the united states need to resume dialogue , seriously consider the common tasks facing the two sides , and find the convergence of interests needed to fulfill these common tasks .
compared with last year 's meeting , the gunpowder smell of this year 's meeting has disappeared , and the positions of the two sides are approaching .
old europe , represented by france and Germany , although still brooding over the us war in iraq , said it wanted to look ahead .
German foreign minister Fischer said at the meeting : " although we have different views on the war , we must work together to ensure peace in iraq after the war , so we must look forward to this .
he also said that although Germany will not send troops to iraq , Germany will not obstruct NATO from playing a direct role in iraq .
the united states , which has seized the lead in the field of modern media , has monopolized a large part of the right to speak in international news . the tentacles of its public opinion propaganda have long spread to the whole world and are almost omnipresent . why is it spending so much money to set up satellite television stations specially covering 22 countries in the middle east ?
in the words of the person in charge of the tongliang no . 1 television station , it is to provide the arab countries with a comprehensive and fair news platform with their own viewpoints .
some analysts have pointed out , however , that " freedom no . 1 " will be a strategic weapon for the united states to infiltrate public opinion , invade culture , and attack the hearts of arab countries . it will also be an important propaganda tool for the united states to pursue a policy of integrating the middle east and transforming the islamic world .
from this point of view , there are roughly three choices for the unique mission of tonglian no. 1 : first , to spread the concept of freedom .
the united states believes that islamic civilization is a serious obstacle for the west to promote modern civilization , and the extremist religious forces in islamic countries in the middle east are hotbeds of international terrorism characterized mainly by opposing the united states . in order to effectively combat terrorism , it is necessary to transform the islamic world so that it recognizes and accepts western values , ways of life , and political systems .
the united states is trying to instill its own ideology in the Arabs through the subtle role played by the tangyo no . 1 program .
the second is to improve the image of the united states .
the united states pursues unilateralism toward the outside world , plays the bully on a series of international issues , and goes its own way . its hegemonic acts have made arab countries and the islamic world angry .
since the september 11 incident , the contradictions between the united states , which has always favored Israel , and the islamic world in the middle east have tended to intensify .
under the pretext of eliminating weapons of mass destruction and anti - terrorism , the united states invaded and occupied iraq by force without conclusive evidence or authorization from the united nations , arousing strong resentment among the muslim people .
the talks between Pakistani and indian officials were held in Islamabad from 16 to 18 february , and hopes for peace once again rose in the south Asian subcontinent .
officials of the two countries set the agenda and format for future talks and established a mechanism for continuous dialogue . this move marked the restart of the dialogue process between Pakistan and india after a two - year hiatus , laid a foundation for the two countries to gradually resolve all outstanding issues , including the Kashmir dispute , and demonstrated the precious peace sincerity of both sides .
prior to the talks , although relations between the two countries had been warmed by a series of good - will moves by both sides , analysts were mostly cautious about the prospects of the peace process .
it is no wonder that looking back at the rapid ups and downs of Pakistani - indian relations in recent years , it seems that no one dares to guarantee that the sunshine shining on the negotiating table today will not turn into lightning and thunder on the border tomorrow .
however , the two countries ' statement read out with smiles on the 18 th by Pakistan 's state secretary for foreign affairs Riyazh Tahokhar has once again spread optimism and brightened the eyes of many people who have been following the situation in south asia for a long time .
first of all , the timetable set for the talks is highly operable . the two sides have not only specified the specific time and topics for the talks , but also stipulated different levels of talks according to the importance of the topics .
second , the two sides have drawn lessons from the failure of the talks caused by the direct dialogue between the leaders of the two countries at the agra summit in july 2001 , and have adopted the method of holding talks step by step so that the talks can be held from a low level to a high level in order to make full preparations for the high - level dialogue .
third , after experiencing several cloudy days in bilateral relations , the two countries unanimously said that war is not a good way to resolve disputes and that the two sides should stay away from war . this consensus has laid the foundation for the leaders of the two countries to reach an understanding that Pakistan and india will never fight again in the future .
to fully and accurately understand and implement the principle of " one country , two systems , " it is necessary to unify the two systems of " one country , two systems , " " one patriotic unit " and " one loving Hong kong , " to unify respect for Hong kong 's high degree of autonomy with the maintenance of state sovereignty , and to unify Hong kong 's capitalism with the adherence to socialism as the mainstay of the country .
only in this way can we earnestly safeguard the well - being of our compatriots in Hong kong and conform to the long - term interests of the country and the entire people .
since Hong kong 's return to the motherland , the central government has unswervingly implemented the principle of " one country , two systems " and acted in strict accordance with the basic law .
the broad masses of Hong kong compatriots enjoy unprecedented democratic rights as masters of the country .
with the vigorous support of the central government and the mainland of the motherland , Hong kong has overcome various risks and challenges , such as the impact of the Asian financial crisis , and continues to maintain its position as an international financial , trade , and shipping center .
practice has proved that the principle of " one country , two systems " has great vitality .
today , we reissued comrade Deng Xiaoping 's speech 20 years ago , which once again declared to the world the firm determination of the central authorities to implement the principle of " one country , two systems " and , still more , to enable everyone to fully and accurately understand the principle of " one country , two systems " and continuously advance the great practice of " one country , two systems " .
