after the 9 / 11 incident , us president bush dished out the strategy of preempting the enemy in june 2002 , put it into practice in us foreign relations , and fought the first preemptive war in iraq in march last year .
the concept of " preemptive attack " not only runs counter to the norms of international law centered on mutual respect for sovereignty and territorial integrity , but will also inevitably lead to dangerous effects of emulation , and a new turbulent situation will emerge in the international order as a result .
in the early days of his preemptive strike theory , some us political leaders raised the following question : what if other countries follow suit one after another ?
of course , over the past two years , more and more countries have claimed to be ready to take the lead , and the number of people who have taken the lead is increasing .
this is a new trend worth paying attention to and studying .
Australian prime minister Howard was the first to show his support when bush put forward the tactic of " taking the lead " .
he said that once reliable information on terrorist attacks on australia is obtained , australia will adopt the tactic of " pre - emptive " against australia and will not hesitate to take military actions in neighboring countries .
he even suggested that the principle of " pre - emptive strikes " should be included in the un charter , arguing that it is necessary to amend the un charter to give countries the right of pre - emptive strikes to crack down on terrorists or countries that support terrorist activities .
in northeast asia , as early as july 1999 , in its " defense white paper , " japan 's defense agency proposed that before facing missile attacks or military incursions , japan could launch pre-emptive strikes against foreign bases .
after the iraq war , japan 's call for a pre - emptive strategy became even louder .
recently , the international public opinion has commented a lot on the current us policy toward africa .
the " foreign policy focus " published by the united states in january this year is entitled " africa policy outlook 2004 . " the article holds that in the past year , the bush administration 's foreign policy has directly or indirectly had a negative impact on africa . in particular , because of the united states ' all - out attention to the war on terrorism and the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction , especially because the united states has no skills in iraq , it has greatly distracted attention from africa .
people still remember that in order to show its concern for africa , the bush administration formulated the president 's emergency plan for aids treatment in january last year , promising to provide africa with at least $ 3 billion a year in funds .
in july last year , president bush visited five african countries , including senegal , south africa , Botswana , uganda , and nigeria , and promised 15 billion us dollars in aid to african countries to fight aids , another 100 million us dollars to fight terrorism in africa , and announced food emergency aid plans , education aid plans , and other aid projects in africa .
at one time , these aid programs were welcomed by african countries and won many international acclaim .
however , a year later , the concrete actions taken by the united states have been delayed .
Africa is in urgent need of assistance .
after entering the new century , africa is facing all kinds of development challenges even more . in order to achieve the development goals set by the united nations for the new century in 2000 , strive to reduce hunger and poverty , and promote health and education , africa has set up the bangladesh african union to coordinate the affairs of the whole continent , and formulated the bangladesh new partnership for africa 's development program aimed at promoting the development of various countries . however , due to its weak economic foundation , development funds have been very short .
the united nations has repeatedly called on developed countries to allocate 0.7 percent of their gdp to official aid to the least developed countries .
however , the united states ' official aid accounted for only 0.1% of its gdp , far short of the united nations ' requirements , and ranked last on the donor list .
recently , european public opinion has been discussing a hot topic : German chancellor Gerhard Schroeder , french president Jacques Chirac , and british prime minister tony Blair 's summit of the three giants is gradually being institutionalized .
public opinion has called Germany , france , and britain , the three big powers , the eu 's new troika , and the relations among the three countries the new triangle .
the new triangle is a new thing , and it remains to be seen where it will go . however , no matter from any angle , on the whole , this new triangle seems to be conducive to the integration process of europe and thus to europe playing an important role in the international arena as a pole in a multipolar world structure .
throughout europe 's 100 - year history , one of the basic characteristics of the german - french - british triangular relations is that britain and france have united , restrained , or resisted Germany .
the two world wars are proof of this .
during the cold war , east and west Germany were pinned down in the Warsaw pact and NATO respectively .
since the end of the cold war , Germany has become stronger after reunification , the western european power structure has become unbalanced , and france has become more suspicious . as a result , the Axis of Zeng , Germany , and france has been dysfunctional for a time , bringing britain and france closer again , and its intention is still to contain Germany .
however , in recent years , with the reactivation of the kosovo - Germany - france axis and the fierce collision of the concepts of unipolarity and multipolarity in the world , the eu has been seriously divided on the iraq issue .
the old Europe , represented by Germany and France , and the new Europe , represented by Britain and Poland , held diametrically opposite positions on the Iraq war .
this split also coincides with the eu 's imminent largest - scale expansion in history .
Egyptian president Hosni mubarak recently made a speech in Cairo on the reform of arab countries , criticizing the outside world for imposing a single reform model on arab countries and warning that such an attempt can only be counterproductive and not conducive to the security and stability of the middle east region .
he held that reform measures should be carried out according to their respective characteristics and capabilities , while a single reform model ignored the cultural background , social customs and religious characteristics of different countries .
at the same time , he pointed out that arab countries welcome foreign help in the reform process , but such efforts should have a clear understanding of different national conditions and respect for the wishes of various countries so as to promote the political , economic , and cultural reform process in arab countries .
the Egyptian leaders ' remarks represent the common views of the arab countries .
at present , under the pressure of anti - terrorism , non - proliferation , and democratic reform , the middle east , as one of the hot spots in the world , is brewing new upheavals and will lead to new integration .
after the wars in afghanistan and iraq , how can iraq , once regarded by the united states as one of the centers of evil , carry out political reconstruction ?
how will the various regimes and social models in the middle east evolve ?
this is of concern not only to the arab world and the international community , but also to the united states and its western allies .
US secretary of state Colin Powell reiterated after meeting with visiting Bahraini crown prince Salman in washington on 9 april that the united states will pursue its plan of democracy and capitalism in a western - style way in iraq and the middle east .
he also stressed that we are considering what else we can do and how to institutionalize these .
last year was the international olympic committee 's year of culture and education .
the beijing organizing committee for the olympic games took advantage of this favorable opportunity to hold a series of educational activities to disseminate advanced culture and popularize olympic knowledge .
among them , the publication of a " textbook on middle school students ' olympic knowledge , " which mainly targets young people , is a very important achievement .
this book is full of pictures and texts . it mainly systematically and vividly introduces the knowledge of the olympic movement and the essence of the olympic spirit in the form of telling stories . it is a good textbook that helps to enhance young students ' understanding of the olympic movement and enhance their enthusiasm for participating in the social olympic games .
last year , the beijing organizing committee for the olympic games specially designed a curriculum made of recycled paper and bearing the emblem of the beijing olympic games for young students .
the idea of a green olympic booth is to prepare for and host the olympic games with sustainable development ideas such as protecting the environment and protecting the ecological balance .
we hope that these curricula will standardize the behavior of young students as stipulated in the class hours , so that they will gradually become practitioners and propagandists of the concept of " green olympic games " .
education is one of the core contents of the olympic games and also an important embodiment of the humanistic olympic games .
the true purpose of the olympic games is to educate young people from a new angle and in a new way and to promote their harmonious physical and mental development so as to contribute to the building of a peaceful and beautiful world .
therefore , the combination of physical education and physical education has not only opened up a new world for the development of education , but also made the olympic games more educational .
this is one of the three major ideas behind beijing 's bid to host the 2008 olympic games .
the core content is to greatly improve the environmental quality of the capital , create a beautiful environment for the olympic games , and build an ecological city .
to this end , it is necessary to extensively adopt environmental protection techniques and means , push forward environmental management , urban and rural greening and beautification , and the development of environmental protection industries on a large scale and in many directions , constantly enhance the whole society 's awareness of environmental protection , and encourage the public to actively participate in various activities to improve the ecological environment .
doing a good job in implementing the " green olympics " is an important task for us to persist in putting people first , establish a comprehensive , coordinated , and sustainable concept of scientific development , and promote beijing 's comprehensive , coordinated , and sustainable economic and social development , as proposed by the third plenary session of the 16th CPC central committee .
we must attach great importance to it .
in order to achieve the goal of a green olympic games , beijing municipality has , on the basis of the " 10th five - year plan " and the " bid report , " compiled the " olympic action plan " and the " ecological and environmental protection plan , " and formulated new targets and plans for environmental construction and protection in the next few years .
through a planned and step - by - step implementation , the goal of holding a green olympic games will be fully realized .
on 25 february , the us state department issued the " country reports on human rights in 2003 , " again commenting on the human rights situation in more than 190 countries and regions , including china . this is exactly the same tone as that of a teacher . the human rights situation in many countries is not good enough to meet us standards and is very bad . some other countries have retrogressed in key areas of human rights , and so on .
of course , there are still countries where the human rights situation has greatly improved , such as afghanistan and iraq , but this is a credit to the us military for overthrowing the former regime and liberating the two countries .
what about the human rights situation in the united states ?
as in previous years , the report did not say a word .
on 1 march , the information office of the chinese state council published the " us human rights record in 2003 , " which made up for the inadequacy of the us human rights report .
based on a large number of facts , the article introduces the existing human rights problems in the united states and the united states ' violation of other countries ' human rights .
in history , Americans have a tradition of stressing honesty and admitting mistakes .
the well - known story of George Washington chopping cherry trees as a child is a vivid example .
now that the united states has become the only superpower in the world , it is no longer telling the truth .
recently , there has been a quiet change in japan 's mainstream media reports on china 's economic development .
contrary to the previous china threat theory , many reports in japan now begin to believe that china 's economic development has promoted japan 's economic recovery , and china 's vigorous market demand has become an important driving force for japan 's economic development .
the us weekly Newsweek also recently carried an article saying that china 's rise is an opportunity and not a threat to other countries , especially neighboring countries .
the much-publicized Theory of the Threat to China is being replaced by the Theory of Opportunity to China .
China threat theory asserts that china 's development will pose a threat to other countries , especially neighboring countries .
yet this provocative assertion has not been accepted by china &apos;s neighbours .
former Malaysian prime minister Mahathir said bluntly that Asian countries need not be afraid of china 's increasing military and economic strength , because china has no tradition of conquest abroad .
the indian defense ministry also held in a long - term plan that china does not pose a military threat to india .
on the economic and trade front , governments and enterprises of all countries regard china as the best choice for expanding the market . overseas investors with strategic vision firmly use their actions to write the theory of opportunities in china : among the top 500 enterprises in the world , more than 400 have come to invest in china .
China has been in the forefront of the world in attracting foreign capital for several years in a row .
GDP is an important macro-economic indicator in the world .
it is of the utmost importance to maintain the growth of GDP in the whole process of modernization in our country .
in view of the fact that every percentage point increase in china 's gdp can correspondingly boost the employment of more than 800,000 people , we must all maintain the momentum of rapid economic growth .
the realization of the grand goal of building a moderately prosperous society in an all - round way and the third - step strategic goal of modernization to a great extent depends on the sustained and rapid growth of the gdp .
however , we should note that GDP indicators are also flawed .
for example , it is not easy to accurately reflect the quality and structure of economic growth , the level of social welfare that people actually enjoy , nor can it accurately measure social distribution and social justice , and so on .
on the other hand , gdp is not the only one .
in assessing our political achievements , we should not only look at the growth of our gdp , but also at the actual material and cultural life of the masses , the employment situation , social security , and even social justice , social order , social management , and social harmony in this region .
therefore , we should treat the existing GDP accounting system with scientific spirit , scientific attitude and scientific method of thinking , and put GDP in a correct position in the overall economic and social development .
while maintaining a certain growth rate , we must not attach too much importance to it , still less one - sidedly and deliberately pursue it .
since the security council delegation visited six west african countries at the end of june last year , the overall situation in the entire region has undergone encouraging changes , although the situation in some individual countries has been repeated for a time .
we are pleased to note that the Government of Sierra Leone is making positive progress in increasing the capacity of the army and police , strengthening control over diamonds in the country and organizing local government elections , and that UNAMSIL is gradually downsizing in accordance with established plans .
it is also reassuring that , with the deployment of UNMIL , Liberia is gradually emerging from the effects of prolonged war and embarking on the path of recovery and reconstruction .
the political process in guinea Bissau has also made positive progress , and the transitional government has pledged to hold legislative elections in march this year .
the peace process in Cote d'ivoire has taken a turn for the better after some setbacks . the parties have pledged to implement the Linas-Marcoussis Agreement , the Forces nouvelles have announced their return to the Government of National Reconciliation , and the Security Council is studying the question of sending a peacekeeping operation to that country .
we look forward to an early decision by the security council on this matter .
the secretariat , ECOWAS and the parties concerned have also worked from a regional perspective to address cross-border issues such as small arms , mercenaries and child soldiers , with positive results .
while fully affirming the above progress , we should note that there is still a fragile side to the overall situation in the west african region . in particular , due to geographical and historical reasons , various countries in the region are closely linked and the situation affects each other . turbulence in one country often affects neighboring countries and even the entire region .
therefore , as recommended in the report of the Security Council , the international community , including the Council , must adhere to an integrated and comprehensive strategy in resolving the problems in West Africa and make great efforts to resolve the relevant cross-border issues . at the same time , it should actively help the countries concerned and regional and subregional organizations such as the African Union and ECOWAS to strengthen their capacity for conflict prevention and resolution .
we have a common understanding that children are the future of the world .
we have an obligation to create the best and most suitable conditions for them to live and study in the interests of their growth , maturity and success .
it was regrettable , however , that in today &apos;s world , millions of children were still suffering from armed conflicts .
they experienced turmoil and backwardness , they saw violence and destruction , they suffered harm and abuse , and they felt sadness and helplessness .
the protection of children from armed conflict was therefore an important responsibility of the international community .
all countries , especially the parties to the conflict , should make the greatest efforts to this end .
we are pleased to see that in recent years the united nations has taken a series of measures to promote the protection of children in armed conflicts and has achieved positive results .
the Council has adopted four successive resolutions , 1261 ( 1999 ) , 1314 ( 2000 ) , 1379 ( 2001 ) and 1460 ( 2003 ) , providing an important framework for the protection of children .
United Nations peacekeeping operations deployed in some regions have made the protection of children an important task , including the appointment of child protection advisers and the full consideration of the special needs of children in assisting host countries in their disarmament , demobilization and reintegration plans .
some peace agreements reached with the facilitation or participation of the United Nations also contain provisions for the protection of children .
national reconciliation is an important condition for the establishment of lasting peace and stability in post-conflict areas .
after the conflict ceases , it will be difficult to truly consolidate the peace situation , and even the flames of conflict may be rekindled , if the parties concerned are unable to discard their old grievances and dispel them .
in many cases , the realization of national reconciliation after a conflict requires the joint efforts of all parties concerned , as well as the support and assistance of the international community , especially the united nations .
over the years , the united nations has played a useful role in helping promote the process of national reconciliation in post - conflict countries , and has accumulated a lot of experience . on the whole , we believe that to successfully help post - conflict countries achieve national reconciliation , the united nations must properly handle the following three major relations :
consider the relationship between immediate needs and long-term goals .
national reconciliation usually takes a certain process and is difficult to achieve overnight .
there should be different priorities at different stages .
to promote national reconciliation , it is first necessary to allow all former combatants to bid farewell to their weapons and create a safe environment .
efforts to disarm , demobilize and reintegrate former combatants are important during this phase .
we are pleased to see that the situation in bosnia - herzegovina has become increasingly stable , relations among all ethnic groups have further eased , economic reconstruction has begun to bear fruit , the return of refugees has been basically completed , and relations with neighboring countries have been improving day by day .
it is gratifying that the peace process in bosnia - herzegovina has made such progress .
we would like to congratulate the government and people of bosnia - herzegovina and sincerely hope that all sides in bosnia - herzegovina will continue their efforts to further strengthen mutual trust and cooperation and continue to push forward the peace process .
at the same time , we also note that institutional and capacity building at the state level in bosnia - herzegovina still needs to be further improved . in particular , reforms in the judicial , police , and other fields are still facing challenges .
we believe it is appropriate for the high representative to make this the focus of his work in the first half of this year , and we support the Bosnian government 's active cooperation with the high representative .
it is believed that with the help of the international community , the Bosnian people will continue to make new achievements on the road of building their own country , embark on the road of independent development at an early date , and further realize the goal of integration into european integration .
peace and stability in Bosnia and Herzegovina are of great significance for the achievement of lasting peace and development in the region .
the chinese side has always followed closely the development of the situation in bosnia - herzegovina and , together with the international community , will continue to make its own contributions to helping bosnia - herzegovina achieve long - term peace and stability and economic development .
China appreciates the efforts made by the CTC to promote the implementation of resolution 1373 ( 2001 ) by all countries and to help strengthen the counter-terrorism capacity of developing countries , and supports the CTC in strengthening coordination and cooperation with relevant international , regional and subregional organizations in the international fight against terrorism .
at the same time , we hope that the CTC will step up its anti - terrorism assistance and make efforts to meet the actual requirements of developing countries .
at present , the issue of revitalizing the Counter-Terrorism Committee has attracted the attention of the vast number of Member States .
following repeated consultations , the CTC submitted its official report , which was circulated as a document of the Council .
through more than two years of practice , the existing structure and modus operandi of the CTC have indeed revealed shortcomings , such as too heavy a reporting burden on Member States , too many meetings and documents , the need to improve the effectiveness of its work , and inadequate coordination among experts .
we therefore fully support the necessary reform of the Counter-Terrorism Committee , we endorse the package proposed in the report , such as the establishment of an Executive Council of the Counter-Terrorism Committee , and we hope that the existing problems , in particular the excessive reporting burden on the general membership , will be properly resolved as soon as possible .
here , i would like to stress that revitalization and reform is an ongoing process and that the CTC should maintain policy guidance and direction in the work of the executive council no matter how it is reformed , and that any decision should be made unanimously and in consultation at the plenary session of the CTC .
in recent years , the issue of small arms has been closely followed by the international community .
this shows that there is a growing awareness of the harm caused by the excessive accumulation of and illicit trafficking in small arms to the stability , post - war reconstruction and social development of the regions and countries concerned .
fortunately , the united nations has taken a series of effective actions to solve this problem .
in 2001 , the " firearms protocol " annexed to the " un convention against transnational organized crime " and the " program of action " on small arms were successively concluded .
it provides a legal and policy basis for properly addressing the problem of small arms and demonstrates the determination of the international community to combat the illicit trade in small arms .
over the past three years , the international community has made great progress in promoting the entry into force of the " Firearms Protocol " and in implementing the " Programme of Action . " in particular , the successful convening of the first biennial meeting of the united nations on small arms in 2003 has provided a new impetus for the continued comprehensive and practical implementation of the " Programme of Action . "
in its resolution 58 / 241 , adopted at the current session , the un general assembly decided to establish a working group to negotiate an international instrument on the marking and tracing of illicit small arms , which will undoubtedly give further impetus to the efforts of the international community to combat the illicit trade in small arms .
similarly , the Council has also paid increasing attention to the issue of small arms and has conducted special deliberations on several occasions and adopted relevant presidential statements and resolutions .
moreover , in its deliberations on a range of issues related to the protection of civilians , women and children in conflict , the Council has stressed the importance of addressing the issue of small arms .
economic development and poverty eradication are the basic prerequisites for achieving sustainable development .
sustainable economic development is the material foundation for environmental protection and all - round social progress .
if we do not resolve the issue of survival , we cannot talk about development , let alone sustainable development .
promoting economic development and striving to eliminate poverty is the only way for developing countries to move toward sustainable development .
without solving the problem of poverty in the developing countries , the development of the developed countries will be difficult to sustain .
rational utilization of resources and protection of the environment are inevitable requirements for achieving sustainable development .
development could not be sustained at the expense of resources and the environment .
natural resources are not inexhaustible and inexhaustible , but the demand for human social development is constantly increasing . if the relationship between the two sides is not properly handled , it will inevitably lead to the deterioration of the ecological environment and seriously threaten the survival and development of mankind .
only by following the path of circular economy based on the most effective use of resources and protection of the environment can sustainable development be realized .
achieving all - round social progress and improving the people 's living standards and quality of life is the ultimate goal of sustainable development .
a year ago , the ninth APEC leaders ' informal meeting was held on the banks of the Huangpu river in Shanghai , and the scene is still vivid to this day .
today , we are gathered in the beautiful los Cabos on the other side of the pacific ocean to discuss the great plan for asia - pacific economic cooperation .
my old friend was very happy to meet me .
I would like to take this opportunity to express my heartfelt thanks to president fox for his gracious invitation and the meticulous arrangements made by the Mexican government .
over the past year , the trend of economic globalization has continued to develop , and scientific and technological progress has changed with each passing day , bringing new development opportunities to various countries .
at the same time , uncertainties in global economic development have increased , and some countries and regions , including relevant APEC members , are facing new challenges in the process of economic development .
protectionism is on the rise again , and there is still a long way to go to achieve free , fair and just trade .
the fight against terrorism was arduous and complex , and non-traditional security factors had increased .
our world is far from tranquil .
although the international community is still facing problems of one kind or another and may encounter problems of one kind or another in the future , the trend of the times for peace and development is irreversible , and the aspirations of the peoples of all countries for a better life have not changed .
the theme of this dialogue meeting is development , which is of great significance .
development is the basis for the progress of human civilization and the key to resolving all kinds of contradictions and problems facing the world .
only by achieving global coordination , balance , and universal development can lasting peace and stability in the world be realized .
we should explore this issue in a comprehensive and in - depth manner and work together to resolve it .
the accelerated development of the trend of economic globalization has become one of the most striking characteristics of the world economy today .
driven by the trend of economic globalization , various countries and regions have become increasingly linked , their markets have become more open , and the flow of funds , technology , and qualified personnel has become more extensive and rapid . all this has brought unprecedented opportunities for strengthening international cooperation and promoting common development .
at the same time , the development of the trend of economic globalization has also brought severe challenges . the gap between the north and the south has widened , some developing countries are in danger of being further marginalized , economic and financial risks have increased , and transnational crimes are serious . all this has increased the urgency of developing international cooperation and jointly meeting challenges .
at this moment when opportunities and challenges coexist , we should seize the opportunities and meet the challenges , seek common ground while reserving differences , expand cooperation , and promote the evolution of economic globalization in the direction of achieving common development and prosperity .
( international ) us flu epidemic peaks
Xinhua news agency , los Angeles , december 31 ( reporter Yan Liang ) - the center for disease control and prevention of the united states said on the 31st that the pandemic flu , which has not been seen in the united states for more than 30 years , has now reached a peak , with 45 out of 50 states in the united states showing a relatively large area of flu spreading and deaths caused by flu increasing rapidly .
according to the center 's statistics as of december 20 , the number of deaths caused by influenza in the united states has reached a record high of 7.8 percent of all deaths in the same period .
at least 42 children across the united states have died of flu and adult deaths have also risen rapidly , but it is not yet possible to accurately count the number of deaths .
experts believe that there are two reasons for the serious spread of influenza in 2003 : first , the flu virus is not the type a flu virus that was prevalent in Panama in previous years , making the vaccines produced earlier unable to effectively prevent the virus , and second , the united states had a surplus of flu vaccines last year , and the two major vaccine suppliers reduced their production to 83 million doses this year , resulting in a shortage of vaccines this year .
although the united states has an average of 36,000 deaths and 114,000 hospitalizations per year , it is still rare for the flu to cause a certain degree of social panic .
William Thompson , an epidemiologist in the united states , said the flu was the worst in the united states in more than 30 years , and it was earlier than in previous years . a large area of flu had spread in many schools , and long queues had been formed in many places where the flu vaccine had been administered .
faced with such a grim situation , the us department of health activated an emergency treatment center on 19 december and dispatched teams of medical experts to various states .
three killed in traffic accident in Zhejiang
Xinhua news agency , Hangzhou , january 1 ( Fang Lie , Zhang hongming ) - an extraordinarily serious traffic accident occurred in Ninghai county , Zhejiang province , in the early morning of the 1 st .
due to heavy fog , an overloaded car collided with a large lorry , killing three people and injuring four others in the car .
at about 2 : 00 am on the 1 st , driver hua drove a red flag taxi , licence plate Zhejiang BT 8705 , from Linhai to Ninghai , carrying six passengers .
at that time , the road was foggy and the line of sight was not clear .
when the taxi reached a distance of 700 meters from the Yonglinline , it collided with a large truck of Hebei 35378 , which was travelling in the same direction .
it was learned that at that time , the large lorry drove from the overpass lane into the main lane , but the taxi could not make way . it crashed from the middle of the lorry into the bottom of the lorry , causing serious deformation of the vehicle . three of the seven people in the vehicle , including the driver , were killed on the spot .
after the accident occurred , the Zhejiang provincial traffic police department promptly issued a circular demanding that the provincial traffic police department immediately take measures to strengthen traffic management under adverse weather conditions , prevent overloading and speeding of vehicles from causing accidents , and ensure road traffic safety during the spring festival transportation period .
( international ) 14 earthquake survivors rescued in iran
Xinhua news agency , Tehran , january 1 , Iranian national radio said on the 1 st that Iranian rescue workers on the 31 st and 1 st successively found 14 more survivors among the ruins of the earthquake - stricken area in Bam .
" we have saved at least one life , " said ali Ashjaa Namadari , a member of the Iranian red crescent society , who rescued a young shop owner from under the wardrobe on the 1 st .
I have been to the battlefield and been tested many times , but i have never been so happy .
Iranian state radio said rescuers also rescued a nine - year - old girl and a pregnant woman from the rubble of the house .
their physical condition is very weak .
rescuers found 11 survivors Monday , including a 4 - month - old baby and an 80 - year - old woman , state radio reported .
but rescuers believe that with the passage of time , the chances of finding survivors are slim .
according to statistics , rescuers have found about 28,000 bodies at the earthquake site and buried some of them .
in addition , they rescued 2,000 survivors from the rubble , most of whom were found the day after the earthquake .
according to the latest report on the earthquake disaster in Bam , iran , released by the united nations humanitarian coordination office on the 31st , the death toll from the earthquake in Bam is expected to rise to 34,000 according to information collected from the earthquake - stricken areas and other sources .
