( international ) US Rescue Team Says Aid to Iran has No Political Color
Xinhua news agency , Bam ( iran ) , january 2 ( reporter Jiang xiaofeng and Liao zhenyun ) - Stef Zaitlin , director of the USAID humanitarian aid project , who is taking part in earthquake relief work in the Bam region of iran , told Xinhua reporters on the 2nd that the us rescue team 's participation in relief activities in iran has no political overtones .
Katrin pointed out that the formation of this rescue team by the us side has nothing to do with politics , and the united states has provided similar humanitarian assistance to iran in the past .
he said the rescue team , composed of 84 people , had set up an urban search and rescue team and a field hospital in the Bam area , and several detachments were responsible for assessing the damage to houses in the city .
they also brought in plastic sheeting , tents and other relief supplies .
asked how long the us rescue team will stay in Bam , Katrin said : " master Chang ( the Iranian government ) will allow us to stay as long as possible . "
Katrin also said that the activities of the us rescue team in Bam were free , and there was no Iranian police to protect or follow them .
in addition , he said , the Iranian government 's response to the earthquake and its ability to deal with the disaster situation are excellent and outstanding .
USAID is a subsidiary of the international development cooperation agency and is under the administration of the us state department .
since the united states and iran severed diplomatic ties in 1980 , the two sides have not resumed normal relations .
the United States still regards Iran as one of the countries that support terrorism and one of the countries that stand on the axis of evil .
the us rescue team came to iran at the invitation of iran 's ambassador to the united nations .
( international ) Israeli deputy prime minister denies plans to expand golan heights settlement
Xinhua news agency , london , january 2 , Israeli deputy prime minister Ehud Olmert denied on the 2 nd that Israel plans to expand Jewish settlements in the golan heights , saying that there is neither such a plan nor such a policy of detente .
Israeli agriculture minister Katz told the media on december 31 that the Israeli government plans to double the number of Jewish settlers living in the golan heights in order to strengthen its control over the golan heights before opening a peaceful dialogue with Syria .
in an interview with BBC , Olmert said Katz was wrong about plans to develop agriculture , tourism and settlements in the Golan Heights .
he said : in the past two days , i have repeatedly verified with the prime minister and the finance minister that according to the government 's commitments , there is no such approved plan .
he said that although some ministers endorsed such plans , the government would never support them .
the golan heights was seized from Syria by Israel during the third middle east war in 1967 , with a total of 17,000 Jewish settlers .
as a result , Syria and Israel have been at war for a long time .
Katz 's remarks on the expansion of settlements in the golan heights immediately aroused widespread international attention . Syria condemned Israel 's intention to expand , stressing that it was illegal .
China &apos;s hi @-@ tech modern weaponry industry is in its infancy
Xinhua news agency , beijing , january 3 ( reporter li zhiyan and li bin ) in the past year , the china weaponry industry group corporation , one of the top 10 military industrial enterprises in china , made great progress in developing and reforming new and high - tech weaponry and equipment to extricate itself from difficulties .
Ma zhigeng , general manager of the china weapons industry group company , said here today that the company 's sales revenue in 2003 was 49.7 billion yuan , an increase of 19.7 percent over the same period last year .
the weapons industry is china 's largest industry in the field of science , technology , and industry for national defense , and has a basic strategic position in national defense modernization construction .
in recent years , the china weaponry industry group company has adhered to the principle of leading in science and technology and putting talented people first . on the one hand , it has grasped the research and development of high - tech weapons , on the other hand , it has grasped the reform and rescue of difficulties , and on the other hand , it has successfully developed a batch of high - tech weapons and equipment urgently needed by the chinese armed forces , thus forming a batch of high - tech military product development and production capacity .
at the same time , the china weaponry industry group corporation made great efforts to carry out structural readjustment , and implemented bankruptcy and closure in a total of 21 enterprises . the total number of employees was reduced from 476,000 at the time of the establishment of the group company to 360,000 , resulting in a net reduction of 116,000 personnel , and six enterprises were reorganized and listed on the stock market .
( international ) Mongolian animal husbandry situation improves in 2003
Xinhua news agency report of january 5 from ulan Bator ( by staff reporter lu guodong ) - according to local media reports on the 5 th , by the end of 2003 , mongolia 's livestock reserves stood at 25,307,800 head , an increase of 1,623,300 head over the same period last year .
this is the first time that Mongolian livestock stocks have rebounded after three consecutive years of drastic decline .
last summer , there was plenty of rain and no heavy snow in spring and winter , creating favorable conditions for the improvement of animal husbandry in mongolia .
by the end of 2003 , the country had 255,600 camels , 1,958,300 horses , 1,784,300 cattle , 10,706,200 sheep and 10,603,400 goats .
compared with the same period last year , the number of camels , goats and sheep increased , while the number of horses and cattle decreased .
Mongolia 's animal husbandry was basically privatized in the 1990 s .
however , after privatization , animal husbandry is entirely dependent on the weather to make a living .
from 1994 to 1999 , Mongolian animal husbandry flourished for six consecutive years due to favorable weather conditions .
at the end of 1999 , mongolia 's animal husbandry reached a record high of 33.5 million head .
however , from 2000 to 2002 , mongolia 's animal husbandry suffered three consecutive years of heavy snow in winter and drought in summer .
at the end of 2002 , there were only 23.6845 million livestock in mongolia , a decline of 9.8155 million in three years .
