( international ) us service industry still lags behind manufacturing industry growth
Xinhua news agency report of january 6th from new york ( by staff reporter Xue Yanping ) - a report released on the 6th by the supply management association , a well - known us research organization , shows that the us service industry index dropped in december last year , indicating that the growth of the service industry is still lagging behind that of the manufacturing industry .
the index of service industries , including retail , financial , construction and other non - manufacturing sectors , fell to 58.6 in december from 60.1 in the previous month , according to the report .
according to the standards of the supply management association , a service index higher than 50 represents industry expansion and a decrease below 50 represents industry contraction .
the us manufacturing index rose sharply in december to its highest level in 20 years , according to another report released by the institute of supply management on Tuesday .
this shows that the growth of the service industry in the united states is still lagging behind the manufacturing industry .
the growth of the manufacturing industry is conducive to expanding employment and promoting economic growth , but the growth of the service industry plays a greater role in reducing unemployment and promoting economic growth .
