( international ) 35 wounded in attack on us military base in iraq
Xinhua news agency report of january 7 from Baghdad ( by staff reporter li jizhi and nie xiaoyang ) - the us military in iraq issued a statement on the evening of the 7 th saying that a us logistics base in western Baghdad was hit by mortar fire that night , injuring 35 soldiers .
at about 0645 local time , unidentified armed men fired mortars at the base and six shells hit the base , the statement said .
at present , the wounded soldiers have been transferred to a nearby field hospital for medical treatment , but the statement did not disclose the condition of the wounded or more details of the incident .
although the shelling did not result in the death of us troops , it was one of the fiercest attacks on us troops in iraq since former Iraqi president Saddam was arrested on 13 december last year .
since the us - british coalition launched the iraq war in march last year , 331 us soldiers have been attacked and killed in iraq .
according to another report , unidentified armed men opened fire on a checkpoint near the northern Iraqi city of Kirkuk on the morning of the 7 th , and then fled .
an Iraqi police officer and a civilian were shot dead .
since the coalition forces occupied iraq , nearly 200 Iraqi police have been killed in various kinds of attacks .
