( international ) Brazil Continue to Fingerprint and Photo Archive American Visitors
Xinhua news agency , rio de Janeiro , january 13 , brazil 's second largest city , rio de Janeiro , continued to fingerprint and archive incoming Americans at airports and ports on the 13th .
in order to mitigate the impact of the move on the tourism industry , the rio de Janeiro tourist office gave small gifts to the incoming Americans to make them feel at home .
the small gifts include a bouquet of bright roses and a t - shirt with the words " love you in Rio de Janeiro " written on it .
the tourism board hopes to ease the burden of waiting in long queues for fingerprints and photos by handing out small gifts to inbound Americans .
Deputy director - general of the tourism bureau Nile Flex said : " this is a subtle welcome and shows how important us tourists are to us . "
he disclosed that about 320 Americans have canceled their travel plans to brazil due to the measures taken by brazil to take fingerprints and photograph and archive Americans .
last year , the us government decided to start taking pictures and fingerprints of foreigners entering the united states , including Brazilian citizens , starting january 5 this year .
in protest against the us move , the Brazilian government has also taken the same measures against Americans entering the country since january 1 .
the us government has repeatedly expressed dissatisfaction with brazil 's practice .
US secretary of state Colin Powell personally called Brazilian foreign minister Amorim this week to demand that brazil abolish this discriminatory measure against Americans .
Amorim asked the united states to take reciprocal action .
