( archaeological discovery ) 31 Qin tombs found in fengxiang county , Shaanxi province
Xinhua news agency report of january 15th from xi'an ( by staff reporter tiema ) - - in the past , historians in fengxiang county , baoji city , Shaanxi province have always believed that the palace district of sun jiatou village was the place where the Qin people moved to Yongcheng , the capital of Shaanxi province , before it became the place for the royal family to carry out major sacrificial activities . however , the Shaanxi provincial archaeological institute accidentally discovered 31 Qin tombs in this palace district a few days ago . it is hoped that this view will be changed .
in order to cooperate with a company in baoji city in building a factory at the site , the Shaanxi provincial archaeological institute conducted archaeological exploration of the site , discovering a total of 31 Qin tombs from the western zhou to the spring and autumn periods in an area of 20,000 square meters urgently needed .
the yongcheng archaeological team in Shaanxi province cleared and excavated these ancient tombs and unearthed more than 40 cultural relics , including bronze ware and pottery .
one of the tombs consists of two coffins and a tomb next to the tomb is a burial pit for two horses .
the tomb unearthed 15 pieces of bronze ware and pottery , including tripods , pots , axes , and so on .
the bronze tripod was well made and beautifully decorated , maintaining the style of bronze ware casting in the western zhou dynasty .
from the objects buried with him , it can be inferred that the owner of this tomb was an aristocrat of the late Western Zhou Dynasty .
experts speculate that there should be a large number of ancient tombs nearby .
this unexpected discovery is of great historical value in studying the relocation of the capital of the Qin dynasty and the layout of the city of Yongcheng during the Qin and han dynasties .
Tian yaqi , associate researcher of the Shaanxi provincial archaeological institute and head of the Yongcheng archaeological team , said : in the past , historians have always believed that the palace area of sunjiatou village was the place where the Qin people moved to Yongcheng , the capital of the city , before it became a place for the royal family to carry out major sacrificial activities during the Qin and western han dynasties .
this discovery shows that this place was a feudal city of the western zhou dynasty long before the relocation of the capital , Yongcheng , and had experienced several flourishing periods .
