China 's tourism revenue is expected to reach 487.4 billion yuan in 2003
Xinhua news agency , beijing , january 22 ( reporter sun yubo ) china 's total international and domestic tourism revenue is expected to reach 487.4 billion yuan in 2003 , 12.4 percent lower than that of the previous year , but the results are better than expected .
statistics provided by the state tourism administration show that the total number of inbound tourists in 2003 was 91 million , including 11.3 million foreigners , 32.7 million overnight tourists , and 17.3 billion us dollars in foreign exchange income from tourism .
the number of domestic tourists was 870 million , and domestic tourism revenue was 344.2 billion yuan , down 0.9% and 11.2% respectively from the previous year .
a responsible official of the national tourism administration said : in 2004 , the tourism industry as a whole will strive for an all - round recovery of the inbound tourism market , continue to promote the prosperity and development of the domestic tourism market , and carry out in - depth the work of rectifying the order of the tourism market .
at the same time , we should do a good job of organizing the theme year of the people 's daily life tour , and concentrate on planning and launching a number of new tourism products that reflect the lives of the chinese people around the theme of the people 's daily life tour .
( international ) economic experts predict the united states to be the biggest winner of us dollar depreciation
Xinhua news agency , Davos , Switzerland , january 23 ( reporter li Jie and ding xigang ) - the 34th annual meeting of the world economic forum , which is being held in Davos , Switzerland , held a special discussion on the 23 rd on the issue of the trend of us dollar depreciation . some experts predict that the united states will be the biggest winner in the continued decline of the us dollar exchange rate .
most economists attending the meeting believed that us officials , including us treasury secretary John Zeno , appeared to have abandoned the strong us dollar policy pursued in recent years .
the weakening of the us dollar will provide the united states with more room for economic development and more employment opportunities , which is evident in the manufacturing industry .
at the same time , the depreciation of the us dollar has made us products more competitive in domestic and foreign markets , which has helped the united states to cover its trade deficit .
however , experts believe that a weak us dollar will also have a negative impact on the united states .
first , the us stock market is likely to continue to be depressed , the value of all kinds of investments will drop , and foreign investors will withdraw their funds out of fear of a further decline of the us dollar . second , more and more expensive imported commodities will eventually lead to a decline in the living standards of Americans . third , the sharp depreciation of the us dollar may also trigger trade and financial turbulence .
but the depreciation of the dollar hit europe , japan and canada harder .
following the decline of the us dollar exchange rate , the pressure on europe 's commodity exports has increased , putting the european economy at risk of being pushed into an all - out recession .
China to speed up development of electronic products in automobile , medical and other application fields
Xinhua news agency , beijing , january 26 ( reporter feng xiaofang ) - china will accelerate the development of automobile electronics , machine tool electronics , traffic electronics , medical electronics , and other applied electronic products to expand the development space of the electronic information industry and meet the needs of various industries .
a relevant responsible person of the ministry of information industry said : in the popularization and application of information technology , transforming and upgrading traditional enterprises is one of the focal points .
promoting the application of information technology in all trades and professions and increasing the market share of domestically produced products and equipment are not only the needs of transforming and upgrading traditional industries , but also bring rare development opportunities to the electronic information industry .
it has been learned that while expanding the development space of the electronic information industry and satisfying the needs of various industries , it is also necessary to support the establishment of a public technical service capability system , support strong hairdressing companies , and provide technical support and guarantee for the application of information technology in key industries by providing technical standards and testing environments .
at the same time , we should develop services such as technical services , management consulting , and system integration , support a number of service enterprises such as system integrators and application service providers , and promote the development of a new information service industry .
( international ) Japanese exports and imports hit record high in 2003
Xinhua news agency , Tokyo , january 26 ( reporter le shaoyan ) - according to statistics released by japan 's finance ministry on the 26th , japan 's import and export trade volume reached an all - time high in 2003 , with the trade surplus once again surpassing 10 trillion yen in three years .
on the export front , japan 's exports to the united states decreased by 9.8 percent last year over the previous year , but its exports to asia increased by 12.9 percent .
this not only made up for the decline in japan 's exports to the united states , but also increased japan 's total exports last year by 4.7 percent over the previous year , reaching a record high of 54.5589 trillion yen .
on the import front , japan 's total import volume in 2003 increased by 5 percent over the previous year to 44.3202 trillion yen , also setting a record high , due to the increase in energy demand , such as oil and natural gas , and the rise in prices .
in 2003 , japan 's trade surplus stood at 10.2387 trillion yen , up 3.6% over the previous year , and surpassed the 10 trillion yen mark three years later .
for the first time , the number of private enterprises in Guangdong has exceeded the number of state - owned enterprises and their holding enterprises .
Xinhua news agency report of january 26th from Guangzhou ( by staff reporter Chen Ji and hu Yanni ) - according to information from the Guangdong provincial administration of industry and commerce , the number of private enterprises in Guangdong exceeded the number of state - owned enterprises and their holding enterprises for the first time in 2003 , and domestic - funded enterprises were effectively adjusted .
according to statistics , by the end of 2003 , there were 690,000 enterprises of all types ( including domestic enterprises , private enterprises , and foreign - invested enterprises ) in the province , an increase of 0.59% over the end of last year .
of these , 316,000 were domestic - funded enterprises , down 16.4% from the end of last year , with registered capital of 119.027 billion yuan , an increase of 0.9% ; 323,000 were private enterprises , with registered capital of 45.228 billion yuan , an increase of 24.9% and 33.8% respectively ; and 52,000 were foreign - invested enterprises , with registered capital of 14.05 billion us dollars , an increase of 3.6% and 4.1% respectively .
for the first time , the number of private enterprises exceeded the number of state - owned enterprises and their holding enterprises .
in the course of structural adjustment , although the number of state - owned enterprises and their holding enterprises has decreased , their actual strength has gradually increased , with the average registered capital ( gold ) per household reaching 3.76 million yuan , an increase of 20 percentage points over the end of 2002 .
according to statistics , in 2003 , there were 105,000 newly registered enterprises of all types throughout the province , showing a drop of one to two liters .
of these , 17,000 were domestic - funded enterprises , down 17.6 percent from the same period last year , and 81,600 were private enterprises and 6,561 were foreign - invested enterprises , up 29% and 0.08% respectively .
the proportion of domestic enterprises , private enterprises , and foreign - invested enterprises in the total number of newly registered enterprises was 1678A . 6 .
( international ) wto has submitted temberd subsidy dispute to arbitration
Xinhua news agency report of january 26th from geneva ( by staff reporter li Jie ) - the world trade organization announced on the 26th that an appeal filed by the eu and seven other wto members for sanctions against the united states for imposing subsidies in temberd has been submitted to an arbitration body for adjudication .
the appeal for sanctions stemmed from the united states ' failure to repeal the Byrd amendment within the time limit set by the wto .
the " bird amendment " passed by the us congress in 2000 requires the us government to directly subsidize punitive duties levied in antidumping and countervailing cases to us companies whose interests have been harmed , rather than turn them over to the us treasury department .
the us move was opposed by major trading partners , including the european union and japan .
in january 2003 , the wto finally ruled that the amendment violated global trade rules and demanded that the united states abolish it by december 27 that year .
however , the united states has not implemented the wto ruling .
for this reason , the eu , japan , canada , brazil , india , the republic of korea , mexico , and chile recently applied to the wto for permission to levy additional tariffs equivalent to the amount of us government subsidies on some products from the united states .
however , the United States subsequently questioned the extent of the sanctions and the legality of the complaint .
( Hong kong , Macao , Taiwan ) Hong kong new year retail business up 10%
Xinhua news agency , Hong kong , january 28 - the Hong kong retail management association disclosed that during the lunar new year period , Hong kong 's retail sales were in an ideal condition , with the industry reporting an increase of 10 percent in average turnover and an increase of 20 to 30 percent in individual shopping malls .
Yu Peng - Chun , chairman of the Hong kong retail trade management association , said a few days ago that mainland tourists ' individual visits to Hong kong have brought along the consumption atmosphere in Hong kong . during the spring festival this year , the retail trade in Hong kong was doing well . some industries , such as jewelry and clothing , saw an increase of 20 to 30 percent . among them , mainland tourists ' consumption accounted for about 10 percent of the total turnover .
he said that the use of renminbi cards by mainland visitors in Hong kong has obviously stimulated the spring festival market , with an average of 3,000 yuan per check - in , and individual mainland visitors spending as much as 10,000 yuan .
Hong kong 's total retail sales fell by 4% last year as a result of the sars epidemic .
Mr yu predicted that with the economic recovery , Hong kong 's overall retail sales would grow by a single digit this year , but commodity prices would also be under upward pressure due to rising costs .
he expressed the belief that deflation in Hong kong would improve this year .
( international ) Denmark Laws New Act to Restrict Immigration
Xinhua news agency , Stockholm , january 28 , Copenhagen : the danish government submitted to parliament on the 28 th a new bill to restrict immigration .
according to the act , children of foreign immigrants born in Denmark will no longer have the right to automatically acquire Danish nationality .
the bill is the latest in a series of immigration restrictions introduced by danish liberal party leader Rasmussen since he became prime minister in november 2001 .
it is reported that the bill is likely to be passed by parliament because the liberal party has the support of the right - wing danish people 's party on immigration issues .
the Act requires the children of foreigners born in Denmark to apply for nationality on reaching adulthood in the same way as other immigrants , rather than automatically acquiring nationality .
migrants who have acquired nationality are deprived of it if they have committed a criminal offence that constitutes a serious danger to society .
in the past two years , the danish government has introduced a series of measures to restrict immigration , including restrictions on the issuance of long - term residence permits and restrictions on immigrants bringing their families into denmark .
the number of foreign asylum seekers in denmark dropped from 14,347 in 1993 to 3,500 in 2003 due to the unwelcome attitude of the danish government towards immigrants .
Denmark &apos;s traditional image as a country of freedom and human rights has also been tarnished .
Singapore &apos;s achievements cannot be taken for granted .
no matter how advanced science and technology are , i do not believe that people can maintain an ideal environment of higher living standards and quality , employment for all , and increasing wages without working hard , maintaining social discipline , and adapting to changes .
these beautiful things do not come naturally .
only when the whole people understand that they must put the interests of the group first , make difficult compromises , and make the necessary adjustments can they bring about a better future for everyone .
what will Singapore be like in a decade or two ?
we all want to see the future , but the future is hard to predict .
many factors are beyond Singapore &apos;s control .
many things depend on the development of the world situation .
we don &apos;t know when it &apos;s going to go wrong and a lot of times it &apos;s luck .
for example , it is unpredictable that three Singaporeans who travelled to Hong kong were infected with the sars virus .
in less than a month after the spring festival , three extraordinarily serious safety accidents have occurred in china , and dozens of people have died each time .
the high frequency of accidents and the heavy loss of life make people sigh .
in the previous few months , the well blowout accident of Chongqing natural gas pipeline , gas explosions in several coal mines , and frequent vicious traffic accidents had caused hundreds of deaths .
China is a country with a vast territory and a dense population , and the probability of disaster is higher than in other countries . it can easily cause the deaths of dozens or even hundreds of people . this is an objective reality that there is nothing we can do about it .
however , judging by common sense , china 's deaths are still too frequent .
among the many disasters , fire , coal mine explosions , firecracker factory explosions , and passenger traffic accidents are the main ones .
this shows at least two problems , one is that security measures in these areas are the weakest , and the other is that people have not learned the lessons from the tragedies of the past , resulting in the recurrence of similar accidents .
in the past , when Singapore 's economy was growing at a high speed , there were serious fire accidents . its painful memory is still deep to this day , but it has also rapidly raised Singapore 's awareness of safety precautions in public places .
China is also in an extraordinary period of rapid economic growth and social transformation .
although the number of accidents involving foreign domestic helpers working in Hong kong is not unusually high in proportion , the relatively safe working environment for domestic helpers is such that the frequency of such accidents is , after all , far from being commensurate with the nature of their work , which has a very low casualty rate .
according to the information provided , from january 1999 to june 2003 , 99 female domestic helpers of various nationalities died in accidents .
behind these figures are broken families that cannot wait for their daughters and mothers to return home , misfortunes that should be avoided , and the direction in which we must try our best to reduce the number of regrets to the lowest possible level .
according to a recent announcement issued by the Indonesian embassy , since 1999 , 96 Indonesian maids have lost their lives while working in Singapore , and some of them have fallen to their death while working in high - rise buildings .
the Indonesian government has voiced dissatisfaction from time to time and has repeatedly enacted new regulations to tighten control over the quality and safety of Indonesian domestic helpers , but the problem has not yet been resolved , and the bilateral relations between new Delhi and india are inevitably beset by the problem of female domestic helpers .
what makes people deeply perplexed is that the number of maids accidentally falling from buildings is unexpectedly higher than the number of casualties among guest workers at construction sites , which makes people think deeply and makes it even more necessary to delve deeper into the background and causes .
Chen kong - li , a well - known expert on the Taiwan issue in mainland china and abroad , recently published his new book " observing Taiwan . "
most of the articles in the book were written after the first change of political parties in Taiwan in march 2000 . up until Chen shui - Bian put forward the theory of " one country on one side of the Taiwan strait , " it was the author 's observation and consideration of Taiwan 's internal situation and cross - strait relations during his stay in Taiwan to listen to his words and watch his deeds .
the article written two years ago was only published two years later . this shows that the mainland has a complicated link in examining the essays and theories on Taiwan - related studies , and the process is a long one . moreover , it shows that " observing Taiwan " did not come easily .
for a long time , in observing and studying the Taiwan issue , Chen Kongli has always been truthful , pragmatic , and seeking truth from facts . he has not been restricted by any subjective predefined political framework . he has also endeavoured to explore the profound insights of those who stand out from the crowd .
after reading this book , this characteristic is even more impressive .
since the early 1980 s , the study of the Taiwan issue has become a mainlander , various research institutions have emerged one after another , and various kinds of scholars and experts have also come to the fore .
overseas , people generally divide Taiwan research institutions in the mainland into northern and southern factions .
the northern faction 's stance is relatively close to the official position and its remarks are relatively hard - line . in certain specific historical stages or in the course of major political developments , the northern faction has shown a more aggressive hawkish tone .
the southernmost Taiwan research institutes are located in areas south of the Yangtze river , including Shanghai and Fujian .
Japan 's prime minister Junichiro Koizumi , who studied in london for two years , was exposed by the Japanese media as exaggerating his academic qualifications .
Japan 's " post weekly " confirmed to the london university 's office of academic affairs that during his nine months in britain , Koizumi attended only a few guest courses at the university and did not receive any degree .
the scandal has been reported or reproduced by china 's media , both large and small , to the great satisfaction of the broad masses of compatriots .
indeed , the prime minister of a prestigious country has gone so far as to fabricate false academic qualifications to deceive his own people .
in particular , it was shameful for japan to take place in the guinea imperialism .
however , if we can change our perspective , we may also see some positive significance from this scandal .
moreover , these positive things are exactly what we lack and what we urgently need to improve .
in recent years , we have always advocated being honest and honest , building a sunny government , respecting the public 's right to know , and enhancing the transparency of administrative units . however , the reality is still far from ideal .
think about it , the diploma of a country 's prime minister is not that big a deal , but it can be exposed by the media and vigorously pursued .
in a country like this , what else can not stand in the sunshine ?
