what should beijing think of the pan - blue forces that may return to power ?
first of all , it should be understood that the pan - blue army , which may return to power , is no longer an exclusive party of the Kuomintang , but a combination of blue oranges , as well as a question of whether internal traditions are in harmony with the natives .
today 's close cooperation during the election period cannot be regarded as an inevitable relationship in the future .
if there is any hope of winning the election , it is bound to take quite some time for internal integration . the upcoming legislative yuan election at the end of the year will also make it very difficult for the lien Chan and Soong regimes to make too major a change in cross - strait relations .
unless it can realize that the improvement of cross - strait relations can add points to Taiwan 's internal politics and is sure to produce results in a short period of time , the most important thing is to let the people feel this result .
based on this background , beijing should temporarily postpone its moves to promote reunification and give lien Chan and Soong , the traditional blue camp leaders , time to consolidate the internal situation .
more than half a century has passed since the united states conducted its first nuclear explosion in new mexico in july 1945 and dropped two atomic bombs on japan in august of the same year .
although the arms race between the two superpowers , the united states and the soviet union , caused nuclear weapons to accumulate to the point of destroying the whole world , fortunately both sides realized the danger of nuclear war and avoided pushing the nuclear button .
after the disintegration of the soviet union and the entry of the world into the post - cold war era , the danger of a large - scale nuclear war was basically eliminated .
at the same time , however , the risk of nuclear proliferation has increased rather than decreased .
this proliferation phenomenon is manifested in two aspects .
first , certain countries at or above the middle level with considerable resources and strength are striving to manufacture and possess nuclear weapons by various means for the purpose of seeking hegemony in the region , confronting neighboring countries , safeguarding security , or pursuing blackmail diplomacy .
another is that some non - state mass organizations , especially islamic extremist forces with strong hatred of the western world , are also doing everything possible to seek small nuclear weapons , not hesitating to harm a large number of innocent people and engaging in bloody terrorist activities against the west .
in light of this demand , intermediaries engaged in the transfer and trade of nuclear weapons and related technologies and the nuclear black market have emerged as the times require . moreover , their scale is increasing day by day , and they have become an important component of nuclear proliferation in the world at present .
as a descendant of the chinese people who grew up in the hangjiahu area , the images of the rural areas in the south of the Yangtze river and the peasants ' lives in the old days are still in my memory .
after many years ' absence , he returned to his hometown and found that the green farmland along the Shanghai - Hangzhou expressway was dotted with three - storey buildings built by peasants themselves , but few people were seen working in the fields .
I am not surprised at this . it is hard to believe that such a great change will happen to our people who are still deeply attached to other countries .
recently , however , i was greatly surprised and shocked to see on the internet some reports on the situation in china 's rural areas , literature and scholars ' on - the - spot investigation reports .
unexpectedly , such an unimaginable dark side still exists in china 's rural areas , and chinese peasants are still living such a humiliating , powerless , and difficult life .
Chen guidi and his wife published a long report entitled " china 's rural investigation " after conducting on - the - spot interviews in the rural areas of Anhui , Henan , and Hebei provinces . they asked for the orders of the peasants and caused a shock in chinese society .
from the large number of facts that the peasants were oppressed and even killed by corrupt officials , they came to the following conclusion : as they approached the chinese peasants , we felt unprecedented shock and secret pain , and we saw poverty , unimaginable evil , unimaginable helplessness , unimaginable struggle , unimaginable silence , and unimaginable sorrow .
this is truly a heartbreaking remark .
not surprisingly , Malaysian prime minister Abdullah announced the dissolution of parliament the day before yesterday , and a new general election will be held in the near future .
for Abdullah , this election will be an event of great significance in his political career , and the result of this election is also of symbolic significance to malaysia 's political situation and its development trend .
Abdullah took over the leadership from Mahathir al - Mahathir in november last year and has only been in power for four months now .
nevertheless , he decided to dissolve the parliament and hold an early general election .
this means at least two things : first , Abdullah is satisfied with his performance in the past four months and is full of confidence in the voters ' intention to vote , and second , he hopes to consolidate his power base in this way so that he can extricate himself from the shadow of Mahathir .
there is no doubt that Abdullah 's decision to hold the blitzkrieg reflects his comprehensive assessment of the domestic political situation .
Malaysia 's current economic situation is doing well , and there are no issues that can be hyped up and exploited by the opposition parties .
moreover , since Adula took office , he has taken a number of highly visible measures in the fight against corruption , including arresting and prosecuting former minister of land and cooperative development Kasida Kaddan on charges of corruption . all these measures have received a certain degree of praise and have made the public optimistic about future anti - corruption actions .
at the same time , he called for enhancing the efficiency of civil service , which was also an encouraging move .
since its birth , the growth and stereotyping of the eu has been strongly influenced by french politics and culture .
in seeking independence and independence in foreign affairs , the attitude and way of handling world affairs should be different from that of the united states . this is the direction of the eu 's foreign policy , and we can clearly see the shadow of france from it .
it is precisely for this reason that the international community , including china , russia , and arab countries , hopes to see the rise of the eu and to see a completely independent force in international exchanges .
it must be admitted that since the late 1980 s , the eu has indeed made diplomatic efforts in this direction .
at the Maastricht summit in december 1992 , eu heads of state unanimously agreed that all member states would implement a unified foreign policy in order to speak to the outside world with the same tone .
however , two years later , when dealing with the Bosnian issue , the so - called unified foreign policy was completely defeated for the first time .
from the Maastricht summit to today , the 10 - year - long eu diplomacy can be said to be unsatisfactory .
in particular , the eu 's foreign policy can not stand the test of major events at all .
the different positions adopted by the member states on the us - iraq war have not only proved this point , but have also fully exposed the fatal flaw of the eu in politics , that is , it is very easy for the eu to be divided and ruled by other big countries and broken down by each other .
on 24 february , president bush announced in the white house that he would support the constitutional amendment banning same-sex marriage .
this is a marked change in his ambiguous attitude on this issue over the past few months and represents an important political development in the us election year .
this constitutional amendment banning same-sex marriage is a very powerful political weapon in the republican party 's new stronghold in the southern united states , but it also has a very negative effect . that is , in the united states as a whole , it is a major cultural dispute dividing public opinion , which will undoubtedly aggravate the polarization of us politics and further alienate the east and west sides of the strait dominated by liberals .
as for bush himself , who repeatedly declared himself to be a rallying cry instead of a rallying cry in the 2000 election , his words and deeds clearly do not coincide .
in addition , the stand of the younger generation of the united states on the gay issue is becoming more and more open . although bush 's move has produced short - term results , it will harm the republican party 's long - term interests .
Bush 's new constitutional amendment offensive can be described as a tangled - earth strategy for this year 's presidential election .
Bush adopted this tactic because he was increasingly in a weak position on two important topics , namely , the war against terrorism and the economy - employment , and had to open up a new battlefield on religious and cultural issues that split public opinion at home .
the attitude of the United States to date has remained cautious .
in other words , since maintaining the status quo in the Taiwan strait can satisfy the long - term goal of the united states of strategically balancing the mainland , the united states should avoid political and military conflicts with china because it encourages Taiwan independence .
it is conceivable that the united states will not completely eliminate the space for Taiwan to hold a referendum in accordance with beijing 's requirements , but out of consideration for its own interests , it will also take some early warning actions .
recently , us secretary of state Colin Powell took the initiative to reaffirm the established Taiwan policy and to express the united states ' stand against Taiwan independence .
this stance has been interpreted by the outside world as aimed at curbing and preventing Chen shui - Bian from going astray .
the recent statements made by some us think tanks with official backgrounds and the fact that the united states will send a large number of spy ships to the Taiwan strait in the near future to detect cross - strait military developments indirectly prove that the united states is very concerned about the situation in the Taiwan strait .
from another angle , it shows that although the united states will not completely prevent Taiwan from holding a referendum as required by beijing , it is also worried about the uncertainty of the situation in the Taiwan strait during this period .
any large - scale one - on - one election can only produce one kind of result in the end , either Chen shui - Bian will be reelected by fluke or lien Chan will re - enter Taiwan 's presidential palace .
what worries people is that under the condition of asymmetrical dissemination of information , people from all walks of life in mainland society seem not to be psychologically prepared for the possibility that Chen shui - Bian may still win .
if the election results are not as desired , it will put beijing in an unnecessary passive position again .
an old Arab proverb says , &quot; A day of chaos is worse than a thousand years of tyranny . &quot;
is this what northeast Asian countries are currently worried about ?
I think the answer is probably yes .
in a recent study , a well - known research and development center near washington and funded by the us government explored four policy options for dealing with the DPRK nuclear crisis , namely , exchanges , containment , economic sanctions , and preemptive attacks .
the attitude of regional countries towards these strategies was the focus of the survey .
in addition , the investigation also analyzed the threat posed by the DPRK 's nuclear weapons program on the basis of the possibility of a nuclear weapons attack by the people of the DPRK 's neighboring countries and the damage they could cause , as well as their fear .
China and russia believe that the danger of north korea using nuclear weapons is low or very low , while the Japanese and south Korean people believe that the threat is quite great .
all Northeast Asian countries are in favour of maintaining contacts with the DPRK .
Japan supports containment , and other countries also believe that containment strategies are acceptable under certain circumstances .
Singapore is very concerned about the international rankings and has been paying close attention to the rankings of various countries published by european and us institutions throughout the year .
being often at the top of the table naturally increases our interest in taking note of the rankings .
but there &apos;s a lot of trouble with being first in everything .
people in general feel that they are afraid of losing if they pay too much attention to rankings , while it is proud to highlight their rankings .
so people say that we should live a more handsome life , and that it is best to be free from the world .
since many people in the past looked down upon the rankings with disdain , a strange phenomenon has emerged : people no longer seem to regard the world 's number one ranger as good news , but rather tend to regard it as an embarrassment .
however , in the past year or two , the situation has changed again .
we are doubtful about the country 's long - term competitiveness , and people in all walks of life are also worried about their own jobs .
with such misgivings , we are no longer speaking in such a smart way .
international competition is fierce , and excessive chic may lead others to catch up head on , and everything will easily become backward in the first place .
