opponents of the us presidential election in 2004 have already decided that democratic candidate Kerry will challenge incumbent republican president bush .
before the november general election , they began such warm - up activities as advertising and election debates .
they will probably engage in verbal and verbal confrontations around the three major topics of war , economy , and society .
Bush believes that the war has a close relationship with us national security , and that sending troops to defeat Saddam Hussein and fight terrorism is to ensure us security , so he keeps telling his countrymen : " we are in the middle of a war . "
Kerry will naturally point out that bush misused the erroneous intelligence that iraq possesses weapons of mass destruction to launch the war against iraq .
speaking of the economy , Kerry believes that bush 's tax cut plan will benefit the rich and will not create new jobs .
Bush asked Kerry to see : are n't the current us economic data going up ?
on social issues , take relations between men and women , bush opposes gay marriage , abortion , and the death penalty , and Kerry opposes gay marriage , but opposes abortion and the death penalty .
how bush and Kerry present and persuade voters with their respective views on these three major issues through advertisements , television , and speeches is the political show they will be performing in the next eight months .
however , on diplomatic topics , Kerry has more room to show off his acting skills .
according to the data , the majority of young people who choose to commit suicide are young people aged 15 to 19 , but there is no shortage of young people aged 10 to 14 .
while academic stress is generally considered to be the leading cause of suicide among children and adolescents , the study found that emotional problems , in particular the problem of love between men and women and the problem of getting along with parents , are the main causes of suicide among young people in Hong kong .
the gap between schoolwork pressure and expectations certainly belongs to the area of communication between parents and children .
the pressure to go to school is an unavoidable burden on the growth of local students , sometimes of their own accord and in many cases imposed by their parents .
parents demand that their children do well in school , compare them with other children at every turn , and urge their children to strive to reach the upper reaches . of course , there is not a small amount of pressure , but the channel of guidance and communication behind the pressure is the thermometer that measures the relationship between parents and children .
if the child 's performance is not up to par , the parents will beat and scold him or give him a silent reprimand , or even let him feel that he is disappointing , and no doubt push him to a hopeless position for help .
it has been learned that many young students in need of counseling have been driven into a corner by their parents ' high expectations and become mentally troubled .
Singapore 's success and rapid development have made parents feel that their children 's material conditions are much better than their own in the past , and it is inevitable that their children should perform better than themselves .
generally speaking , parents forget that when they were children , in fact , their performance in various fields may not be particularly outstanding .
by the age of one and a half , the vast majority of children are sent to day-care centers in various government agencies under the system of full child care . the authorities only charge a nominal child care fee , and the children only return home one day a week or even a month .
today , Singapore faces the social problems of declining fertility and an ageing population .
in order to maintain a modern standard of living and fashionable material enjoyment , the younger generation has no energy to respond to the government 's call for early marriage and childbearing .
the author has a bold suggestion : the government should come forward and accept the newborn children .
our countrymen only manage their students and do not have to worry about the issue of parenting .
on the one hand , the government has set up a full - time nursery school , converted primary schools to full - time schools , and even provided three meals , symbolically charging citizens an affordable fee .
this will not only solve the employment problem of the unemployed , but the government will also not have to worry about the effectiveness of such measures as baby bonuses , increased maternity leave , the quality of female domestic workers , and tax rebates .
what beijing needs to do is not only to act as the leader of the six - party talks , but also to focus on china 's long - term interests on the Korean peninsula , prepare for a rainy day , and make strategic arrangements as soon as possible .
specifically , on the one hand , beijing wants to urge the DPRK to give up its nuclear weapons ; on the other hand , it wants to start with reforming Kim Chong - il 's regime to lead it onto the path of modern civilization , dispel the danger of a nuclear war in northeast asia , maintain the status quo on the Korean peninsula , and gain bargaining chips for a long - term strategic maneuver with the united states .
Pyongyang is a bully with a deep desire to develop its economy and integrate into the international community .
however , this desire is often manifested in a forceful , irrational , and sometimes totally incompatible form with international rules .
in fact , for some time now , beijing has been using its influence and economic aid means to force Pyongyang to change its stance that does not conform to international rules .
however , this operation still needs to be planned in all directions .
Beijing 's assistance to Pyongyang should not be limited to the economic level , but should extend to other areas of society , and should not be limited to Pyongyang 's abandonment of its nuclear program , but should focus on leading it onto the path of modern civilization .
