China 's policy of reform and opening up began with agriculture , and rural residents were the earliest beneficiaries of this policy .
however , after the 1990 s , agricultural reform was basically at a standstill because of a large bias in economic policies in favour of cities , and the gap between urban and rural areas became increasingly wide .
over time , china will present two very different worlds , one is a highly prosperous city and the other is a poor and backward country .
in the official words of china , the widening gap between the rich and the poor in china 's urban and rural areas is a developing problem , so it should be solved through sustained development .
that is to say , china 's coastal areas and cities should continue to develop and should not be affected by rural problems .
however , when people see that some major cities can change from year to year and from year to year , they cannot help asking : why have there been no changes in some impoverished areas in the past few decades ?
of course , the paths of development in urban and rural areas are very different . this is a fact that should be acknowledged . however , the question is whether the rural population , which accounts for 70 percent of the total population of the country , has also been cared for and valued while investing a great deal of money in urban construction and providing encouragement and support to the wealthy middle class .
theoretically , successive chinese governments have attached great importance to agricultural , rural , and peasant issues .
over the years , however , the situation in the rural areas has become increasingly difficult and worsening , which shows that the importance attached to the rural areas has become less and less serious .
in any country , public security , procuratorial , and judicial organs should be symbols of justice and fairness , and they should also be the most important systems for ensuring social stability .
unfortunately , however , public security , procuratorial , and judicial organs have become symbols of corruption in china .
according to a recent report by the state auditing administration , the results of last year 's examination of the financial expenditures of public security organs in 26 provinces and municipalities showed that the amount of public security violations nationwide reached 16.5 billion yuan .
the crisis of trust in the public security , procuratorial and judicial organs has become public .
the liu yong incident , the sun Zhigang incident , and the recent Heilongjiang tongbaoma incident all reflect this deep mistrust .
the Tseng BMW incident is even more typical .
much more attention has been paid to this problem than even during the SARS roundup .
as a matter of fact , people 's concern is no longer the tan BMW incident itself , but an expression of mistrust of the entire judicial system .
the departments concerned were very clear about this , so they soon took measures to ban the media .
but there is still the problem .
the second round of six - party talks on the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula ended in a generally expected outcome .
during the talks , the parties concerned made contacts and tentative explorations on the peripheral issues of the nuclear crisis on the peninsula , and reached consensus on holding a third round of talks and establishing a working group before the end of june this year .
however , on substantive issues such as how the DPRK should abandon its nuclear weapons development program , how the united states should ensure the DPRK 's political and military security after the DPRK abandons its nuclear program , and how it should provide energy assistance to the DPRK , the talks not only failed to make progress , but also gave the impression that the deadlock was getting more and more tense .
neither north korea nor the united states has shown any concession , and neither side has relaxed its basic stance .
what attracts people 's attention , however , is that the united states showed an attitude of not rushing to resolve the issue during this round of talks , giving people the impression that it is dragging its feet .
the tactics displayed by the united states are closely related to the new developments in the current international situation and the interests it is seeking in these new developments .
never before in the history of Roosevelt &apos;s presidency have so many corporate bosses been in jail .
is this a coincidence , or has the public and investors over the past three years become intolerant of corporate crimes and other illegal activities , leading to the concentration of these crimes being exposed one after another recently ?
the answer may not be simple , but it is true that many companies ' criminal activities have been exposed recently .
this augurs well for economic recovery , especially for restoring investment confidence .
the late 1990s may have been one of the most chaotic and elusive periods in us commercial history , and the sooner the effects dissipated , the better .
when the dust settles , the names of some companies will fade into history , and in the end they will only be found in business school textbooks .
other companies , such as Tyco and MCI , under the leadership of the new management team , will try to reorganize themselves to usher in a new round of economic growth .
when will a new round of economic growth arrive ?
as CEO , you may not have an answer .
it doesn &apos;t matter because Fed Chairman Greenspan doesn &apos;t know the answer either .
the bush administration wants to use Keynesianism to stimulate the economy by , on the one hand , vigorously increasing spending ( especially on national defense ) and , on the other hand , greatly reducing taxes .
on the international front , the bush administration continues to promote free trade , but the trade deficit has reached a new high of $ 549 billion .
after the substantial tax cuts , investment and consumption did not increase significantly .
the new Keynesian school , represented by the famous british economist Wyme Godley , believes that the us economy is already in trouble and that bush 's financial and economic strategy is ineffectual .
they held that the so - called " commanding of the law of the market " is only an illusion , which is bound to lead to profits for a small number of people and losses for the majority .
people used to believe that on a global scale , the so - called minority of the profiteers are in the united states , and the majority of the losers are in developing countries .
at present , this is not the case .
many people in the us economic circles believe that besides us - based multinational companies , india and china are also in a prominent position as the current winners of globalization .
India occupies the service economy , while China occupies the manufacturing sector .
people are concentrating their attention on the phenomenon of the massive transfer of us funds and production equipment to china , but they do not see the advantages of china 's high - level , low - income labor market .
first , whether the current situation in Taiwan is within beijing 's estimate or beyond beijing 's estimate .
Beijing only knows its own estimates , but others can judge the results from the open phenomenon .
over the past four years , the Chen shui - Bian and Annette lu independence camps have spoken clearly , acted diligently , and made positive progress in their Taiwan independence moves .
on the other hand , except for the occasional high - pitched tone , beijing 's attitude is almost routine , and it seems indifferent to the progress of Taiwan independence .
however , since last fall , it has changed drastically , as if cattle carts were turned into cars , which has been noticeable for several months , and the handling capacity is quite different from that of the 1990 s .
it can be inferred from this that the current situation in Taiwan is within its estimate .
second , look at Taiwan - related diplomacy .
as for the development of the situation in the Taiwan strait , it depends on whether the attitude of the united states and other major countries is relatively close to beijing or Taipei .
since the attitude of all countries is open and visible , the answer is very clear .
so far , not only have countries and beijing become closer and more concretely intersect , but they have become farther apart and less concretely intersect with Taipei . moreover , they have also begun to give advice to Taiwan 's democracy , which has always been praised .
